(299, 0, 299, NULL, NULL, 'Add isis and protostar to testing sample data extension table', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-04 18:27:19', '2012-08-04 23:48:59', '2012-08-04 23:49:08', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/299.diff'),
(300, 0, 300, NULL, NULL, 'JHTML::image() can return a bad image link', '<p>When calling JJHTML::image() with $relative set to true, a bad image link is created in administrator when an image file exists only in JPATH_THEMES . "/$template/$folder/system/$file".</p>\n\n<p>Discussion and test file at <a href="http://forum.joomla.org/viewtopic.php?f=579&amp;t=734663">http://forum.joomla.org/viewtopic.php?f=579&amp;t=734663</a></p>\n\n<p>Cause:<br>\nSee the statements at about line 417 of /libraries/joomla/hmtl/html.php</p>\n\n<pre>\n// Try to deal with system files in the template folder\nelseif (file_exists(JPATH_THEMES . "/$template/$folder/system/$file"))\n{\n    $includes[] = JURI::root(true) . "/templates/$template/$folder/system/$file";\n    break;\n}\n</pre>\n\n<p>The file is detected in /$template/$folder/system/$file but the link builds as webroot/$template/$folder/system/$file. In administrator, the link should be built as webroot/administrator/$template/$folder/system/$file instead.</p>\n\n<p>Solution:<br>\nChange</p>\n\n<pre>\n    $includes[] = JURI::root(true) . "/templates/$template/$folder/system/$file";\n</pre>\n\n<p>To:</p>\n\n<pre>\n    $includes[] = JURI::root(true) . ($app-&gt;isAdmin() ? ''/administrator'' : '''') . "/templates/$template/$folder/system/$file";\n</pre>\n\n<p>To be honest, I don''t know how this scenario would exist unless someone moved an image into /templates/$template/$folder/system. But, I thought I''d post this in case someone ran across it or the developers wanted to do a fix.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-04 21:59:27', '2012-12-28 21:41:46', '2012-12-28 21:41:46', NULL),
(301, 0, 301, NULL, NULL, 'Newsfeeds Update to Use JFeed', '<p>This updates the newsfeeds component and feed module to use JFeed rather than SImple Pie since Simple Pie is throwing so many strict errors.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-05 02:19:23', '2012-08-09 04:28:14', '2012-08-09 04:28:14', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/301.diff'),
(302, 0, 302, NULL, NULL, 'More updates of Hathor', '<p>This finishes up (I think) making all of the layouts render adequately although there still remain an number of issues.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-05 19:57:36', '2012-08-05 20:17:13', '2012-08-05 20:17:13', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/302.diff'),
(303, 0, 303, 25295, NULL, ' [#25295] Email exposed through RSS and Atom feeds', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=25295">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=25295</a></p>\n\n<p>The diff will apply to both 2.5.x and master.</p>\n\n<p>This patch extends Elin''s pull/282 to correct author name and email for weblinks and contacts.  The user id was previously displayed when there was a blank Created By Alias.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-07 14:10:12', '2012-08-11 16:16:45', '2012-08-11 16:16:45', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/303.diff'),
(304, 0, 304, NULL, NULL, 'Modified the regular expression in language debugger to include dot sign as a valid KEY character', '<p>More info: <a href="http://code.joomla.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28908">http://code.joomla.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28908</a></p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-08 18:07:46', '2012-12-28 21:41:22', '2012-12-28 21:41:22', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/304.diff'),
(305, 0, 305, 28912, NULL, '[#28912] Simplified regex to prevent stack overflow on long strings', '<p>Simplified the regex checking for an escaped double-quote by handling it the same way as <em>QQ</em>.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-12 14:50:04', '2012-12-28 21:40:59', '2012-12-28 21:40:59', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/305.diff'),
(306, 0, 306, NULL, NULL, 'Update com_newsfeeds and mod_feed to use jfeed', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-12 15:28:51', '2012-08-25 05:47:24', '2012-08-25 05:47:24', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/306.diff'),
(307, 0, 307, NULL, NULL, 'PostgreSQL driver for Joomla! CMS 3.0', '<p>This driver implements inherited function from JDatabase class and add some other useful function to be able to use Joomla! on PostgreSQL database.<br>\nThere is also a class that inherits from JDatabaseQuery to be able to create query object using PostgreSQL dialect.<br>\nAlso added change item class for Postgresql under CMS libraries folder.<br>\nThis pull include codes from platform 12.1 for JDatabaseQuery::charLength to address CMS'' CASE WHEN<br>\nqueries that has to be compared with 0 .</p>\n\n<p>JDatabasePostgresql::getQuery has an optional second parameter to retrieve JDatabasePostgresqlQuery object, used inside JDatabasePostgresql::insertid call .</p>\n\n<p>PostgreSQL''s added functions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>getRandom, ge a random number</li>\n<li>getStringPositionSQL, returns string''s position inside another string</li>\n<li>releaseTransactionSavepoint, release given savepoint during transaction</li>\n<li>showTables, lists all table in database</li>\n<li>transactionSavepoint, to create a savepoint</li>\n</ul><p>Overridden functions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>connected</li>\n<li>dropTable</li>\n<li>escape</li>\n<li>explain </li>\n<li>fetchArray</li>\n<li>fetchAssoc</li>\n<li>fetchObject</li>\n<li>freeResult</li>\n<li>getAffectedRows</li>\n<li>getAlterDbCharacterSet</li>\n<li>getCollation</li>\n<li>getCreateDbQuery</li>\n<li>getNumRows</li>\n<li>getQuery</li>\n<li>getTableColumns</li>\n<li>getTableCreate</li>\n<li>getTableKeys</li>\n<li>getTableList</li>\n<li>getVersion</li>\n<li>hasUTF</li>\n<li>insertid</li>\n<li>insertObject</li>\n<li>lockTable</li>\n<li>query</li>\n<li>queryBatch</li>\n<li>renameTable</li>\n<li>replacePrefix</li>\n<li>select</li>\n<li>setUTF</li>\n<li>test</li>\n<li>transactionCommit</li>\n<li>transactionRollback</li>\n<li>transactionStart</li>\n<li>unlockTables</li>\n<li>updateObject</li>\n</ul><p>PostgreSQL database query added functions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>limit, a possible replace for limit in setQuery</li>\n<li>offset, a possible replace for limit in setQuery</li>\n<li>forShare, lock table/row during SELECT</li>\n<li>forUpdate, lock table/row during SELECT</li>\n<li>noWait, no wait a locked table</li>\n<li>returning, an INSERT INTO optional clause to returns last insert id</li>\n</ul>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-15 16:24:40', '2012-09-06 14:46:54', '2012-09-06 14:46:54', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/307.diff'),
(308, 0, 308, NULL, NULL, 'Change the variable name on the submenu rendering to avoid conflicts', '<p>$this-&gt;modules was already in use in some of the managers so switched it to $this-&gt;submenumodules in all the managers to avoid the conflicit.</p>\n\n<p>JHtml::_(''behavior.modal''); is also added to the menu manager so that the modal link to the modules will work</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-16 07:27:02', '2012-08-16 14:14:21', '2012-08-16 14:14:21', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/308.diff'),
(309, 0, 309, NULL, NULL, 'Add Protostar and Isis to the database.', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-16 12:20:49', '2012-08-16 14:15:20', '2012-08-16 14:15:20', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/309.diff'),
(310, 0, 310, NULL, NULL, 'Update sample data for Isis and Protostar', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-16 16:18:58', '2012-08-17 00:21:43', '2012-08-17 00:21:43', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/310.diff'),
(311, 0, 311, NULL, NULL, 'Fix for missing labels', '<p>Hi, </p>\n\n<p>J3 Alpha 2 works flawless. I''ve fixed the missing labels in the spanish installer.</p>\n\n<p>Thanks,<br>\nAnibal</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-17 13:46:26', '2012-08-17 16:51:49', '2012-08-17 16:51:49', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/311.diff'),
(312, 0, 312, NULL, NULL, 'Fix type attributes not required in html5. Thanks @nternetinspired', '<p>Issue reported by <a href="https://github.com/nternetinspired" class="user-mention">@nternetinspired</a> in the template9 branch:<br><a href="https://github.com/Joomla3-Admin-template/joomla-cms/issues/114" class="issue-link" title="Type attributes are not required in html(5)">Joomla3-Admin-template/joomla-cms#114</a></p>\n\n<p>To enable the html5 mode in the template use:</p>\n\n<pre><code>JFactory::getDocument()-&gt;setHtml5(true);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The type attributes will dissappear.</p>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-08-18 00:56:57', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-08-20 14:11:49', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/312.diff'),
(313, 0, 313, 28929, NULL, '[#28929] Missing </div>. Corrected indenting.', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-18 13:20:26', '2012-08-18 15:38:26', '2012-08-18 15:38:26', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/313.diff'),
(314, 0, 314, NULL, NULL, 'Component options button routing error', '<p>Component options button routs to the appropriate page but then it never returns it to the page it came from  with save&amp;close/Cancel like the j2.5 did. Need to add a way to know where the person is coming to the page from.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-18 13:26:25', '2012-12-28 21:39:44', '2012-12-28 21:39:44', NULL),
(315, 0, 315, 28849, NULL, '[#28849] Publishing date instead of creation date in article category feed', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28849">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28849</a></p>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-08-18 14:16:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-08-18 14:16:11', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/315.diff'),
(316, 0, 316, NULL, NULL, 'Added colors to main icons in admin (isis)', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-19 21:06:18', '2012-08-26 09:21:36', '2012-08-26 09:21:37', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/316.diff'),
(317, 0, 317, NULL, NULL, 'Added ordering to column titles where it was missing', '<ul>\n<li>Added ordering to column titles where it was missing</li>\n<li>Fixed incorrect icon when ascending</li>\n<li>Added correctly formatted tooltips to order column titles</li>\n<li>Fixed classnames on many column titles</li>\n<li>Fixed ordering on some components</li>\n<li>Fixed some html issues</li>\n<li>Made the order direction filter a little wider so the text does not get cut off</li>\n</ul>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-20 12:24:56', '2012-09-06 10:17:04', '2012-09-06 10:17:04', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/317.diff'),
(318, 0, 318, NULL, NULL, 'Backport fix for transcode from the Platform', '<p>Fixed in:Â <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/commit/0a1a641494ba26449b029bd10a119bb4e9cc37bd" class="commit-link">joomla/joomla-platform@<tt>0a1a641</tt></a><br>\nResolves:Â <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/179" class="issue-link" title="Bug in libraries\\joomla\\utilities\\arrayhelper.php on line 463">joomla/joomla-cms#179</a></p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-22 06:47:33', '2012-11-18 04:27:31', '2012-11-18 04:27:31', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/318.diff'),
(319, 0, 319, NULL, NULL, 'move the </h2> to the right location in featured intros ', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-22 07:40:10', '2012-08-23 21:11:19', '2012-08-23 21:11:19', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/319.diff'),
(320, 0, 320, NULL, NULL, 'Fixed Lithuanian installation language file', '<p>I fixed  file in order to match constants with Joomla 3.0 version. There were missing many strings. <br>\nAlso tweaked some already translated strings, because they were not precise and translated by absolute amateurs.</p>\n\n<p>I''m native Lithuanian speaker which lives here and knows Lithuanian language perfect</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-08-22 13:24:27', '2012-12-28 21:39:33', '2012-12-28 21:39:33', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/320.diff'),
