(349, 0, 349, NULL, NULL, 'Added support for multiple tabs with options in the template styles manager', '<p>Earlier the template style edit page showed always all options in the<br>\none "Options" tab. Implementation is based on the edit view from the<br>\ncom_modules manager.</p>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-09-04 18:50:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-09-09 16:06:14', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/349.diff'),
(350, 0, 350, 29069, NULL, 'Joomla CMS [#29069] Sort by Status does not work', '<p>Link to the tracker:<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29069">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29069</a></p>\n\n<p>The bug:<br>\nSort by Status does not work.  I can''t click on the Status column in plugin<br>\nmanager or module manager to sort by that column.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-04 20:29:57', '2012-09-05 07:16:12', '2012-09-05 07:16:12', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/350.diff'),
(351, 0, 351, NULL, NULL, 'Category/Featured content layouts should pass entire article object to onContentPrepare method', '<p>Tracker: [#27699] Only text gets passed to content events in blog view<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=27699">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=27699</a></p>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-09-05 10:17:24', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-09-05 10:17:24', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/351.diff'),
(352, 0, 352, NULL, NULL, 'Beez Update', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-05 13:02:49', '2012-09-05 22:37:43', '2012-09-05 22:37:43', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/352.diff'),
(353, 0, 353, NULL, NULL, 'Joomla 3 Error', '<p>Just unzipped the Joomla 3.0 alpha 2 release and I receive this error when trying to access it:<br>\nParse error: syntax error, unexpected T_CONST in /index.php on line 10</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-05 14:41:30', '2012-09-05 20:16:42', '2012-09-05 20:16:42', NULL),
(354, 0, 354, NULL, NULL, 'Update sample data', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-05 17:11:57', '2012-09-06 14:45:49', '2012-09-06 14:45:49', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/354.diff'),
(355, 0, 355, NULL, NULL, 'Inconsistent refreshManifestCache and manifest files load', '<p>I just found an inconsistency on installer and refresh manifest function... when installing an extension it gets the first valid manifest xml... ok, but if the file is not  mod_xxxx.xml e.g: if the xml file is manifest.xml, the refresh cache will not get it... refresh cache requires a xml file named as extension name, but that file can not exists some times... so I think we should fix that updating the extensions adapters to use the jinstaller findManifest function instead of look for a specific filename... I have fixed it and will make a pull request.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-05 17:44:39', '2012-09-05 20:46:40', '2012-09-05 20:46:40', NULL),
(356, 0, 356, NULL, NULL, 'Inconsistent refreshManifestCache and missed manifest file for modules, component and plugins', '<p>Fix the issue #355 about inconsistent refreshManifestCache.</p>\n\n<p>It was looking for a fixed file name for manifest, instead of use the installation behavior, to use the first valid manifest file found. </p>\n\n<p>If someone install an extension with a manifest.xml instead of mod_myext.xml, it''s ok, until the user refresh the manifest cache or try to add a module (joomla will not find the right manifest file).</p>\n\n<p>For modules, components and plugins.</p>', 3, 0, 1, '2012-09-05 18:12:20', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-09-10 16:13:35', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/356.diff'),
(357, 0, 357, NULL, NULL, 'Update Beez for Joomla 3', '<p>Change to beez3 and add bootstrap calls</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-05 22:34:11', '2012-09-06 14:47:46', '2012-09-06 14:47:46', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/357.diff'),
(358, 0, 358, NULL, NULL, 'Implementing basic HTML5 semantic markup', '', 3, 0, 1, '2012-09-06 00:14:05', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-09-06 12:51:47', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/358.diff'),
(359, 0, 359, NULL, NULL, 'CS clean up plus jquery fix in beez3', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-06 02:28:23', '2012-09-09 16:34:11', '2012-09-09 17:24:30', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/359.diff'),
(360, 0, 360, NULL, NULL, 'Error on login to backend', '<p>When I login to the backend I receive a 500 error with a message saying:</p>\n\n<p>SQL=UPDATE <code>__session</code> SET <code>guest</code> = ''0'',   <code>username</code> = ''[DATA REMOVED]'',  <code>userid</code> = [DATA REMOVED] WHERE <code>session_id</code> = ''[DATA REMOVED]''</p>\n\n<p>If I refresh the page everything seems to work fine and I''m logged in, but I still get this error every time I login</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-06 10:17:24', '2012-09-06 15:22:43', '2012-09-06 15:22:43', NULL),
(361, 0, 361, NULL, NULL, 'LESS Compiler', '<p>If there is a LESS compiler built into Joomla, how can I call it from my template?</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-06 16:25:42', '2012-12-28 21:51:19', '2012-12-28 21:51:19', NULL),
(362, 0, 362, NULL, NULL, 'Fix check for New button in some views', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-07 08:35:33', '2012-09-17 13:34:41', '2012-09-17 13:34:41', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/362.diff'),
(363, 0, 363, NULL, NULL, 'Removes <strong> from module chrome markup', '<p><strong> is a semantic element, not a presentational one. For stylistic purposes simply set font-weight in css instead. It''s use in this context is incorrect.</strong></p>\n\n<p>See: <a href="http://html5doctor.com/i-b-em-strong-element/">http://html5doctor.com/i-b-em-strong-element/</a> for details.</p>\n\n<p>Semantically, it would be preferable to wrap the module header in a   element too of course. </p>\n\n<p>I shall submit an additional PR with suggested improvements to the module markup. </p>\n\n<p>Thanks.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-07 08:43:26', '2012-09-07 09:10:51', '2012-09-07 09:10:51', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/363.diff'),
(364, 0, 364, NULL, NULL, 'Module save2copy dont work', '<p>(PHP Notice: Undefined property:ModulesModelModule::$input) &gt; (Fatal error: Call to a member function get() on a non-object in .../administrator/components/com_modules/models/module.php on line 896)</p>\n\n<p>On click ''Save as Copy'' throws an error.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-07 12:39:01', '2012-09-08 22:40:15', '2012-09-08 22:40:15', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/364.diff'),
(365, 0, 365, NULL, NULL, 'Accordion fieldsets for template and category options like com_menus ', '<p>Also included is a bootstrap.endAccordion markup fix. That destroies the layout (e.g. currently in the menu manger)</p>\n\n<p>The pull request enables an accordion on category and template options. By default it looks like to make no sense, but if some extension extend fieldests with jform plugins then it will be mess.</p>', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-07 14:08:11', '2012-09-09 09:53:46', '2012-09-09 09:53:46', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/365.diff'),
(366, 0, 366, NULL, NULL, 'Changed default frontend template from Beez3 to Protostar', '', 3, 0, 10, '2012-09-07 15:49:58', '2012-09-10 10:04:10', '2012-09-10 10:04:10', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/366.diff'),
