(3174760, 42, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>Do you mean the tracker on joomlacode.org? I''ve tried to use it before but I can''t stay logged in. Practically every page load loses my session. It''s super annoying. </p>', '2011-12-16 08:44:23'),
(3178210, 43, 'severdia', '<p>The PSD should be zipped, not removed. And you can''t remove legal material from the distro.</p>', '2011-12-16 15:11:17'),
(3179416, 43, 'oc666', '<p>I don''t think we this source folder because it doesn''t used by the Joomla system.</p>', '2011-12-16 16:41:19'),
(3192038, 30, 'eddieajau', '<p>Method signature fixed.  Also added missing bits to the Hathor users view, default layout.  However, I''m not familiar with what is required for new view layouts in Hathor (not sure that''s really my responsibility, but anyway).  If there''s documentation you can point me to to guide me through how to do that I can take a stab at it, otherwise I think that should be the responsibility of the experts that maintain Hathor (in which case, just shoot me a pull request).</p>', '2011-12-17 22:55:43'),
(3193266, 45, 'elinw', '<p>i''m sending this because Michael is in transit and I wanted to make sure it gets in on time.<br>\nThe sql is updated in a way that assumes that user notes is going to be merged with the changes to sql that are in that pull request.</p>\n\n<p>The sample data sql enables finder and the corresponding plugins and front end module. I''d suggest this for testing during the beta period and then a decision can be made about whether to have them enabled in the release packages.</p>\n\n<p>For testing, please start by clicking on the indexer in the Finder adminstrator. This could take as long as several minutes to run. At that point the features can be tested.</p>', '2011-12-18 05:06:04'),
(3193619, 44, 'infograf768', '<p>Please post this proposal on Joomlacode tracker with test instructions. This filed is not present in joomla.sql</p>', '2011-12-18 07:44:14'),
(3193915, 44, 'mbabker', '<p>We''ve had a tracker item for months on this that''s gone untested.  Care to take a look?  <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=26635">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=26635</a></p>', '2011-12-18 09:37:53'),
(3195206, 30, 'chdemko', '<p>Ok, I will ask Andrea to create the layout for Hathor.</p>\n\n<p>Currently, the pull request cannot be merged</p>', '2011-12-18 15:24:14'),
(3197316, 30, 'eddieajau', '<p>Merge conflict fixed.</p>', '2011-12-18 22:19:14'),
(3197569, 35, 'realityking', '<p>Closing since this has been committed.</p>', '2011-12-18 23:06:30'),
(3197593, 30, 'realityking', '<p>A suggestions for the future: Could we please only merge big pull requests like this after they''ve been rebased into just a couple of commits (the less the better, but at least one per author is required). This would make the commit history much more meaningful and easier to read.</p>\n\n<p>It''s really not needed to follow how a feature grew to be, when I browse the history I just wanna see the when the feaute hit the repro.</p>', '2011-12-18 23:10:59'),
(3197612, 45, 'realityking', '<p>I''d really like to see this one rebased as well. It makes for a much nicer to read history.</p>\n\n<p>Also this contains a platform change, that one should probably first be submitted upstream.</p>', '2011-12-18 23:13:30'),
(3197832, 47, 'realityking', '<p>Note the required SQL changes are still missing, I could use some help there.</p>', '2011-12-18 23:55:12'),
(3214013, 42, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>OK, well, I guess this bug will go unreported and unfixed because your tracker site doesn''t work properly. Do you have a tracker for your tracker? Maybe I can report a bug there.</p>', '2011-12-20 03:41:00'),
(3215077, 42, 'elkuku', '<p>Ah come on, please don''t give up so quickly :)<br>\nThe CMS is in a state of "transition". The tracker on joomlacode.org is somewhat "old" and is going to be replaced soon - At least that is what they are saying... We are all waiting eagerly to fill this space here with pull requests because it seems that there are a lot of people getting very comfort with git and GitHub.<br>\nBTW: The code enhancements you are proposing for CodeMirror are looking quite good :) I would recommend though not to mix "topics". This allows for easier testing and further merging of your code.</p>\n\n<p>Keep going, pls ;)</p>', '2011-12-20 06:12:48'),
(3215136, 42, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>It''s no problem. I can wait until joomlacode.org gets updated if that''s what''s required. I have several other enhancements to various parts of the system as well. I''m a big fan of Joomla and I hope to help make it even better. </p>', '2011-12-20 06:21:37'),
(3216204, 29, 'infograf768', '<p>Copying Module and changing language without changing position just changes the language of the module chosen</p>', '2011-12-20 08:55:37'),
(3216851, 45, 'infograf768', '<p>Language issues:<br>\nBack-end filters are double translated.<br>\nTake off true in<br>\n&lt;?php echo JHtml::_(''select.options'', JHtml::_(''finder.mapslist''), ''value'', ''text'', $this-&gt;state-&gt;get(''filter.branch''), true);?&gt;<br>\nand<br>\n&lt;?php echo JHtml::_(''select.options'', JHtml::_(''finder.statelist''), ''value'', ''text'', $this-&gt;state-&gt;get(''filter.state''), true);?&gt;<br>\nRemains Country an Region to deal with in Maps Manager. as 2 strings are missing:<br>\nCOM_FINDER_TYPE_P_COUNTRY="Country"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_TYPE_P_REGION="Region"</p>\n\n<p>Front-end<br>\nSame issue: take off true in<br>\n$html .= JHtml::_(''select.genericlist'', $nodes, ''t[]'', ''class="inputbox"'', ''id'', ''title'', $active, ''tax-'' . JFilterOutput::stringUrlSafe($bv-&gt;title), true);</p>', '2011-12-20 10:05:38'),
(3217363, 45, 'infograf768', '<p>// Activate the highlighter if enabled.<br>\nif (!empty($this-&gt;query-&gt;highlight) &amp;&amp; $this-&gt;params-&gt;get(''highlight_terms'', 1)) {<br>\n    JHtml::_(''finder.highlighter'', $this-&gt;query-&gt;highlight);<br>\n}</p>\n\n<p>breaks search results here.</p>\n\n<p>IT looks also, here, that starting typing for joomla for example does not any more present a list of results dropping down from the search field</p>', '2011-12-20 11:03:22'),
(3221060, 45, 'elinw', '<p>JM do you mean you are not getting suggested search terms? </p>\n\n<p>Chris, next time you might want to try a rebase, but all that happened is that the project cms has had tons of updates and you got them all. </p>\n\n<p>The highlighter issue should be fixed now.</p>', '2011-12-20 16:22:02'),
(3227134, 49, 'realityking', '<p>9 commits for a one line change? Whoever commits this, please don''t just merge, apply it manually. Thanks. :)</p>', '2011-12-20 23:22:28'),
(3228823, 49, 'elkuku', '<p>Well, I realized after submitting the pull that the branch contains also previous work done to the debug plugin. But I suppose it will be applied as a <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/49.diff">patch</a>, so history is lost anyway ;)<br>\nBut in fact it is all related to the debug plugin.. </p>', '2011-12-21 02:50:40'),
(3229107, 46, 'dextercowley', '<p>This has been committed. Thanks!</p>', '2011-12-21 03:35:00'),
(3230450, 45, 'infograf768', '<p>Missing taking of ''true'' line 371 of<br>\nJROOT/components/com_finder/helpers/html/filter.php</p>\n\n<p>should be:<br>\n$html .= JHtml::_(''select.genericlist'', $nodes, ''t[]'', ''class="inputbox"'', ''id'', ''title'', $active, ''tax-'' . JFilterOutput::stringUrlSafe($bv-&gt;title));</p>\n\n<p>In the same file change line 369 to<br>\n$html .= JText::sprintf(''COM_FINDER_FILTER_BRANCH_LABEL'', JText::_(''COM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_''.$bv-&gt;title));</p>\n\n<p>to be able to use the strings:<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_AUTHOR="author"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_CATEGORY="category"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_COUNTRY="country"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_EVENT="event"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_ISSUE="issue"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_LABEL="label"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_REGION="region"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_QUERY_FILTER_BRANCH_TYPE="type"<br>\netc.</p>\n\n<p>I still can''t get autocompletion here.</p>', '2011-12-21 07:06:16'),
(3230491, 45, 'infograf768', '<p>Also joomla.sql not installing finder correctly here. Had to discover.</p>', '2011-12-21 07:13:56'),
(3230515, 45, 'infograf768', '<p>Also, still missing in back-end<br>\nCOM_FINDER_TYPE_P_COUNTRY="Country"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_TYPE_P_REGION="Region"</p>', '2011-12-21 07:17:35'),
(3235245, 45, 'infograf768', '<p><a href="https://github.com/test" class="user-mention">@test</a> a clean install of finder-Integration Finder-Integration-joomla-cms-1611287.tar.gz<br>\nchange of plugin folder (I guess) has broken the finder plugins<br>\nIndexing broken too</p>', '2011-12-21 15:43:54'),
(3235511, 45, 'infograf768', '<p>After changing back the plugin folder to finder, all works fine here, including auto-completion.<br>\nAll finder stuff is installed as should although it was decided that the plugins would be disabled by default, if I remember well. Also I see that the site module has been published.<br>\nCommitter: this needs an update sql in com_admin</p>', '2011-12-21 16:04:16'),
(3239816, 29, 'mbabker', '<p>Fixed issue with module copy/move.</p>', '2011-12-21 21:23:54'),
(3243348, 51, 'elinw', '<p>I''m not sure what to do here, the firt parts of this have been merged.</p>', '2011-12-22 02:50:22'),
(3254141, 54, 'dextercowley', '<p>Committed via patch. Closing. Thanks!</p>', '2011-12-22 20:06:14'),
(3254142, 53, 'dextercowley', '<p>Committed via patch. Thanks!</p>', '2011-12-22 20:06:29'),
(3258529, 57, 'elinw', '<p>I know this is wrong, just trying to get the files straightend out.</p>', '2011-12-23 06:49:28'),
(3258533, 56, 'infograf768', '<p>Thanks. Fixed via patch. Closing.</p>', '2011-12-23 06:49:58'),
