(3278013, 42, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>So, is this tracker issue getting fixed? Is anyone else even having the same trouble? </p>', '2011-12-27 01:44:25'),
(3281711, 60, 'mbabker', '<p>It looks like you need to rebase your branch onto joomla/master.  There are many files being showed as modified that were already committed.</p>', '2011-12-27 14:25:10'),
(3283534, 62, 'gnomeontherun', '<p>I''ve also removed the PDF cheatsheet and replaced it with a RESOURCES.txt file, like the other documentation files in the src folder for blueprint.</p>', '2011-12-27 17:47:30'),
(3291867, 62, 'gnomeontherun', '<p>This should also be noted, their Wiki lists resources, and has a list of templates for various CMS and framework platforms, however Joomla is not even listed? <a href="https://github.com/joshuaclayton/blueprint-css/wiki">https://github.com/joshuaclayton/blueprint-css/wiki</a></p>', '2011-12-28 15:37:54'),
(3312615, 29, 'chdemko', '<p>The pull request cannot be merged<br>\nCould you make a pull request on the platform for the changes?</p>', '2011-12-30 11:41:15'),
(3314890, 29, 'mbabker', '<p>The changes to JControllerForm are already in the platform (not sure why it didn''t merge in on the last platform merge).  The fix for the user list I''ll take care of later.</p>\n\n<p>Merged from master, so should merge cleanly for a short time.</p>', '2011-12-30 17:00:58'),
(3320559, 29, 'infograf768', '<p>Don''t want to be pushy, but this patch includes a lot of new language strings and we get nearer to beta2 /RC.<br>\nWe will have to declare a language freeze at some time.</p>', '2011-12-31 09:37:30'),
(3320561, 64, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker on joomlacode for this to be tested.</p>', '2011-12-31 09:38:54'),
(3322053, 29, 'mbabker', '<p>I''ve just pushed the last set of fixes for the issues <a href="https://github.com/chdemko" class="user-mention">@chdemko</a> reported.</p>\n\n<p>Can we merge soon?</p>', '2011-12-31 17:27:32'),
(3323258, 67, 'mbabker', '<p><a href="https://github.com/oc666" class="user-mention">@oc666</a> you need to either use a separate branch (<code>git checkout -b &lt;new_branch_name&gt;</code>) or remove the commit for the Blueprint changes.  You''ve got both in this pull request, which is incorrect.</p>', '2011-12-31 23:22:14'),
