(4967453, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>I noticed that the ''delete'' function in the file controller and the folder controller seem to be basically the same. Why not make both of these classes inherit from MediaController and put the delete function there instead?</p>', '2012-04-05 02:34:58'),
(4969448, 181, 'infograf768', '<p>Please opem a tracker on joomlacode and reference here.</p>', '2012-04-05 06:46:46'),
(4969503, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>I would be happy to do that if only I could stay logged in to joomlacode long enough. I have posted here multiple times about this problem. Am I the only one? I log in, click a link or two and suddenly I''m logged out again. It happens no matter what browser I use, whether I access from home or work, mac or windoze. Does that site actually function for some people? What''s the secret? </p>', '2012-04-05 06:53:07'),
(4978413, 178, 'piotr-cz', '<p>It''s possible to upload multiple files using Flash uploader (Administration &gt; Content &gt; Media Manager &gt; Options, haven''t tested) but I''d prefer html5 way.</p>', '2012-04-05 15:08:12'),
(4987870, 177, 'projeteweb', '<p>Tracker<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28363">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28363</a></p>', '2012-04-05 23:11:38'),
(4989093, 178, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>I don''t necessarily have an opinion about keeping or dropping the Flash uploader. I only think it makes sense to use the full capabilities of HTML whenever possible. </p>', '2012-04-06 01:11:45'),
(5008671, 174, 'infograf768', '<p>Committed through eclipse.</p>', '2012-04-07 14:46:06'),
(5008802, 179, 'infograf768', '<p>Can you indicate how to reproduce this issue</p>', '2012-04-07 15:02:38'),
(5034570, 184, 'billrich', '<p>$doc-&gt;addStyleSheet should be used -- see patches pending for beez and hathor to correct loading of stylesheets and js in those templates - better to include fix also for atomic </p>', '2012-04-09 21:43:22'),
(5040802, 179, 'mickles', '<p>I have this annoying bug too :(</p>\n\n<p>The bug was appered after last update to 2.5.4<br>\nI can''t figure out how to reproduce it. Only if I send you the full site copy.<br>\nThis message is shown at the top of an admincenter, on all pages except home.<br>\nIf somebody tell me how to identify a source of the problem so I can debug it with Eclipse PDT</p>\n\n<p>So I going to restore to 2.5.3 </p>', '2012-04-10 07:55:45'),
(5048152, 185, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a Tracker on joomlacode with test instructions and add references here</p>', '2012-04-10 15:12:44'),
(5050609, 186, 'davidhavard', '<p>Ignore - found how to override this now.</p>', '2012-04-10 16:55:51'),
(5051883, 184, 'elinw', '<p>Hi Bill,</p>\n\n<p>JM was already asked to do that for Atomic as part of his other patches. This just addresses the positions issue and as noted in the tracker item there will probably be some additional work once this is merged.</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28382">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28382</a></p>', '2012-04-10 17:52:42'),
(5051951, 172, 'elinw', '<p>merged</p>', '2012-04-10 17:55:13'),
(5052224, 181, 'elinw', '<p>You usually have to log in twice. No idea why but it seems to work.</p>', '2012-04-10 18:06:47'),
(5054764, 185, 'wdaniels', '<p>Logged at joomlacode.org #28391</p>', '2012-04-10 19:56:35'),
(5060719, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>Well, look, I managed to fight my way to the tracker submission page (twice) and submit the issue. But, of course, I was logged out as soon as I clicked the submit button and the issue did not appear in the list. </p>\n\n<p>Is there any person actually responsible for joomlacode who I could get some support from? Or was that site just set up years ago and left to rot? I see that issues have been posted to the tracker as recently as yesterday (or maybe it''s today, I''m probably a day ahead) so it seems to work for somebody. What is the secret? No, logging in twice doesn''t change a thing. </p>\n\n<p>Actually, I can go into more detail about the login problem. If I log in at <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/account/?action=Login">http://joomlacode.org/gf/account/?action=Login</a> I will get in and be redirected to ''My Page''. But almost any action gets me logged out and sent back to the login page with a ''redirect'' parameter. If I submit the login form while that parameter is in the url, I will always just end up back at the same login form. The only way I can successfully log in is to remove that parameter, but then I end up back at ''My Page'' and unable to get to other pages without being logged out again. I''m trying to be patient with this thing but it''s quite frustrating. </p>', '2012-04-11 02:00:25'),
(5068208, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>i got this problem as well...</p>\n\n<p>i''m using windows, zend server, php 5.3.3 </p>\n\n<p>hope somebody able to solve it</p>', '2012-04-11 13:05:58'),
(5068253, 179, 'atomtech', '<p>I get this same problem too!</p>\n\n<p>i''m using windows, zend server, php 5.3.9!</p>', '2012-04-11 13:08:46'),
(5072938, 179, 'infograf768', '<p>At looking on the Net, it could be related to the use of Zend.</p>', '2012-04-11 16:32:29'),
(5073844, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p><a href="https://github.com/brunoferrari" class="user-mention">@brunoferrari</a> <a href="https://github.com/mickles" class="user-mention">@mickles</a> - do you guys use Zend Server as well ? </p>', '2012-04-11 17:14:53'),
(5084913, 188, 'infograf768', '<p>Please post a tracker on joomlacode and reference here.</p>', '2012-04-12 05:49:14'),
(5084981, 179, 'infograf768', '<p>See:<br><a href="https://bugs.php.net/bug.php?id=50688">https://bugs.php.net/bug.php?id=50688</a></p>', '2012-04-12 05:58:15'),
(5085305, 179, 'mickles', '<p>```infograf768 commented <br>\nSee:<br><a href="https://bugs.php.net/bug.php?id=50688">https://bugs.php.net/bug.php?id=50688</a></p>\n\n<pre><code>\nso possibly the patch is:\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I turned off warnings with ini_set before calling usort, then turned them on again after.<br><br>\nThis is an effective workaround for now, but I''d love to clean that nastiness out of my code.</p>\n\n<pre><code>\nI''ll try it a little bit later...\n</code></pre>', '2012-04-12 06:41:40'),
(5085340, 179, 'mickles', '<p>And yes, I use windows\\zend </p>\n\n<pre><code>PHP Built On\n\n Windows NT MICKLES7 6.1 build 7601 \n\n\n\nDatabase Version\n\n 5.5.12 \n\n\n\nDatabase Collation\n\n utf8_general_ci \n\n\n\nPHP Version\n\n 5.2.17 \n\n\n\nWeb Server\n\n Apache/2.2.16 (Win32) mod_ssl/2.2.16 OpenSSL/0.9.8o \n\n\n\nWebServer to PHP Interface\n\n cgi-fcgi \n\n\n\nJoomla! Version\n\n Joomla! 2.5.3 Stable [ Ember ] 15-March-2012 14:00 GMT \n\n\n\nJoomla! Platform Version\n\n Joomla Platform 11.4.0 Stable [ Brian Kernighan ] 03-Jan-2012 00:00 GMT \n\n</code></pre>', '2012-04-12 06:45:46'),
(5085431, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>i wonder if the bug is within the php itself, people should ''scream'' at the moment, but in fact it happen to most zend server user.... </p>', '2012-04-12 06:54:03'),
(5086946, 188, 'sybrek', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28398">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28398</a></p>', '2012-04-12 08:49:03'),
(5091928, 181, 'elinw', '<p>Yes it works really well for dozens of people everyday.  I''ve asked Sam to take a look at if there is a problem with your account. </p>', '2012-04-12 14:17:43'),
(5106189, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>elinw, thanks, I hope it can be fixed soon. </p>\n\n<p>realityking, thanks for the feedback. I think I should first modify the upload function so that it works whether Filedata is an array or not (well, it''s always an array but you know what I mean). After that, it will up to the template to either use this feature or stick with single file uploads. As to the doctype, do you know if there is any plan to switch to HTML5 or any reason not to do so? </p>', '2012-04-13 00:30:09'),
(5106409, 181, 'realityking', '<p>I''m pretty sure we''re gonna switch to the HTML5 Doctype for 3.0, not sure we wanna touch that for 2.5.</p>\n\n<p>Personally I don''t mind the invalid attribute too much, also I''d be willing to trade the small change required to layout overrides for simpler code but at the end that''s a call to be made by leadership.</p>', '2012-04-13 00:49:38'),
(5106418, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>Oh, and I''ve added a couple of functions but I didn''t add a ''<a href="https://github.com/since" class="user-mention">@since</a>''. What will be the next version?</p>', '2012-04-13 00:50:05'),
(5106544, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>As you can see, getting it to work properly whether or not multiple is set in the template doesn''t really complicate the code in any significant way. Probably better to be a little more robust and backward compatible here. That being said, the built in templates don''t seem to override this page. Maybe some 3rd party ones do? Are there 3rd party admin templates? </p>', '2012-04-13 01:00:46'),
(5109189, 189, 'infograf768', '<p>Please add a tracker on joomlacode and put reference here</p>', '2012-04-13 06:36:38'),
(5110031, 190, 'infograf768', '<p>Please cretae a tracker on Joomlacode and add reference here.</p>', '2012-04-13 07:52:17'),
(5110065, 190, 'fititnt', '<p>This <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28403">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28403</a> ?</p>', '2012-04-13 07:55:33'),
(5112953, 189, 'rvsjoen', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28404">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28404</a></p>', '2012-04-13 11:42:21'),
(5113256, 190, 'garyamort', '<p>Note: the point of it not being of type submit in that instance is because it is not allowed to have no search terms specified.  It prevents the user from submitting the form if they don''t enter anything.  There is an onclick javascript which modified it from to a submit button when data has been entered.   As such, for a small change it is better to make it of type button rather then submit.  Mind you, I think it''s better to validate server side and always let it be a submit button - use the javascript onClick event to validate, but for those who have javascript disabled let them submit and catch it server side.  But that''s a more involved bit of code.</p>', '2012-04-13 12:04:49'),
(5115081, 191, 'infograf768', '<p>Please make a tracker on joomlacode and add reference here.</p>', '2012-04-13 14:01:25'),
(5116606, 191, 'mbabker', '<p>This code should actually be removed.  The <code>$_observers</code> array in JDispatcher is protected and unable to be accessed from the indexer helper.</p>\n\n<p>The best practice is for plugins to check for the <code>com_finder.indexer</code> context.  Otherwise, there really isn''t anything that can be done within the indexer''s code.</p>', '2012-04-13 15:12:32'),
(5122615, 191, 'garyamort', '<p>"Please make a tracker on joomlacode and add reference here." - no. :-)</p>\n\n<p>Sorry, I lack the time to learn how to navigate yet another system.  I''ll offer the change for those who decide they want it.  Beyond that though I lack time.</p>', '2012-04-13 18:48:11'),
(5122841, 191, 'garyamort', '<p>'' The $_observers array in JDispatcher is protected and unable to be accessed from the indexer helper.''... hmm, it worked for me.  I must have subclassed the JDispatcher class in order to get around that..  ugly hack...  I guess I could go back and swap it out calls to detach instead...  I''ll put that on my todo list.....  low, but there. :-)</p>', '2012-04-13 18:59:18'),
(5145850, 190, 'fititnt', '<p>I realized that beyond the problem of validation, Joomla 2.5.4, when accessed via IE7 (at least via IE9 with browser mode IE7), com_finder component button does not work. Test can be done on <a href="http://demo17.cloudaccess.net/using-joomla/extensions/components/search-component/smart-search.html">http://demo17.cloudaccess.net/using-joomla/extensions/components/search-component/smart-search.html</a> . With enter on text field still working. This happens because IE7 need that button element has an explicit value  equals to "submit" on type. So at least commit:137d207, the fist of this thread, solve this.</p>\n\n<p>On commit:e7d5cd7 already has javascript to enable and disable submit via button and via pressing enter on input search field on component, and make possible change minimum length via template override, but still not make any additional check on back end, but I can do it.</p>\n\n<p>Anyway. is allowed (or not a bad idea) to change "Allow Empty Search" or even add a new option on backend of com_finder for 2.5, or must wait for 3.0? Could be interesting to make possible flexible minimum length, because just one letter still more than one empty value, and at least two letters appears more reasonable.</p>', '2012-04-16 05:06:36'),
(5146083, 190, 'mbabker', '<p>Seems like sound logic to me.  I''ll test later on my Windows system to see how things behave.</p>', '2012-04-16 05:39:09'),
(5149338, 185, 'infograf768', '<p>Please let it know in the tracker when ready to test.</p>', '2012-04-16 10:11:31'),
(5163769, 181, 'realityking', '<p>There are a few other admin templates, for example <a href="http://adminpraise.com/">AdminPraise</a>.</p>', '2012-04-16 22:05:35'),
(5165489, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>I see. Well, in any case, this change should not break the functionality of any template.</p>', '2012-04-17 00:04:14'),
(5175983, 192, 'infograf768', '<p>This issue has already been committed to Platform and is RTC in jjomlacode.<br>\nSee: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28364">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28364</a></p>', '2012-04-17 14:15:41'),
(5194580, 159, 'infograf768', '<p>Committed via eclipse.</p>', '2012-04-18 09:09:14'),
(5208570, 154, 'ercanozkaya', '<p>Those who need to work this around can use something like this: <br>\nJFactory::getSession()-&gt;set(''com_docman.fix.the.session.bug'', microtime(true));</p>', '2012-04-18 20:55:42'),
(5209256, 154, 'oc666', '<p><a href="https://github.com/ercanozkaya" class="user-mention">@ercanozkaya</a> don''t forget to update you session table to be able to contain all the microtime:<br>\nALTER TABLE #__jos_session MODIFY COLUMN time varchar(15) DEFAULT '''';</p>', '2012-04-18 21:29:20'),
(5209318, 154, 'ercanozkaya', '<p><a href="https://github.com/oc666" class="user-mention">@oc666</a> Not needed for the workaround. This just changes something in the session data so that the database query will return an affected row.</p>', '2012-04-18 21:32:32'),
(5221635, 193, 'dgasparri', '<p>getInstance() should also be cleaned and simplified, as it does stuff proper of a factory pattern and factory method (choosing which class to load). Not knowing if there was backward compatibility issues, I left it like that.</p>\n\n<p>Part of the "reasoning" in getInstance() about the environment variables ($_REQUEST task, controller, option, and so on) are left intact in the getInstance(), but were duplicated cleared and streamlined into the createEnvironmentArray() method.</p>', '2012-04-19 13:36:22'),
(5235930, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>Slight change of subject so maybe I should start a new thread but <a href="http://filepicker.io/">this</a> looks pretty good. I might try to write a module for it if I have some spare time. Any thoughts?</p>', '2012-04-20 00:52:09'),
(5244993, 195, 'Balleno', '<p>query in business.php:</p>\n\n<p>$db-&gt;setQuery("SELECT #__bd_packages.picture_num FROM #__bd_businesses<br>\nLEFT JOIN #__bd_packages ON #__bd_packages.id=#__bd_businesses.package_id WHERE<br>\n#__bd_businesses.id=".JRequest::getVar(''id''));</p>', '2012-04-20 14:21:45'),
(5266934, 194, 'dgasparri', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28441">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28441</a></p>', '2012-04-22 10:39:06'),
(5266939, 193, 'dgasparri', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28441">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28441</a></p>', '2012-04-22 10:39:35'),
(5282120, 196, 'florianv', '<p>2 Â° commit) I think the $strict param complicates things for nothing, and is never used in any "core extension" call.<br>\nMoreover, I don''t get why the OR is there, because it''s independent from the frontend/backend.</p>', '2012-04-23 14:21:58'),
(5295445, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p><a href="https://github.com/elinw" class="user-mention">@elinw</a> Any word from sam about this joomlacode problem?</p>', '2012-04-24 00:55:03'),
(5329567, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>Any update ??</p>', '2012-04-25 12:05:28'),
(5329773, 185, 'wdaniels', '<p>Revised as <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/198" class="issue-link" title="SQL Portability Patches">joomla/joomla-cms#198</a></p>', '2012-04-25 12:20:21'),
(5333518, 197, 'infograf768', '<p>Ryan, pelase create a joomalcode tracker and cross-reference here,</p>', '2012-04-25 15:10:02'),
(5333593, 197, 'ryandemmer', '<p>The tracker already exists, I have posted a response to it - <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=27711">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=27711</a></p>', '2012-04-25 15:12:59'),
(5366917, 113, 'Bakual', '<p>Is there no interest in this simple and small fix?</p>\n\n<p>I''m a bit confused that neither the trackeritem nor the pull request here gets any attention.</p>', '2012-04-26 20:27:09'),
(5394825, 188, 'infograf768', '<p>Committed with eclipse. Thanks.</p>', '2012-04-28 06:29:35'),
(5394851, 160, 'infograf768', '<p>Thanks. Fixed through eclipse.</p>', '2012-04-28 06:35:10'),
(5506760, 200, 'infograf768', '<p>Please, if not done, open a bugtracker on joomlacode with precise test instructions and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-05-04 09:07:37'),
(5506893, 201, 'infograf768', '<p>This option is not used in core. It is a remnant of an attempt to get better SEO in a pre-1.6 stable version.<br>\nBugsquad tests have shown that using this may have weird results.</p>\n\n<p>If it can be demonstrated that this is the main culprit for the option, generally speaking, please open a tracker on joomlacode.</p>', '2012-05-04 09:19:13'),
(5507187, 197, 'infograf768', '<p>Please separate issues. We are here dealing with the sef plugin only.<br>\nI suggest you first propose the new library function to platform.</p>', '2012-05-04 09:41:15'),
(5507398, 197, 'ryandemmer', '<p>Sorry I don''t know how to separate the requests and I didn''t realise Github would add them together.</p>\n\n<p>Should I close and re-open the pull request?</p>', '2012-05-04 09:55:18'),
(5507620, 197, 'realityking', '<p><a href="https://github.com/infograf768" class="user-mention">@infograf768</a> you should be able to just apply this patch: <a href="https://github.com/ryandemmer/joomla-cms/commit/f811241c5432521c3979d0ba1a40c6ed34612ee5.diff" class="commit-link">ryandemmer/joomla-cms@<tt>f811241</tt></a></p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/ryandemmer" class="user-mention">@ryandemmer</a> If you make a pull request based on a branch all new commits you push into that branch will be part of the pull request</p>', '2012-05-04 10:13:54'),
(5512669, 200, 'seanredmond', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28497">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28497</a></p>', '2012-05-04 15:16:09'),
(5513557, 197, 'infograf768', '<p><a href="https://github.com/ryandemmer" class="user-mention">@ryandemmer</a> <br>\nas it is a library file patch, I suggest you create a pull to platform first.<br>\nLet''s keep this one as is. I will close it after committing the part needed.</p>', '2012-05-04 15:50:11'),
(5514099, 201, 'bembelimen', '<p>Hello,</p>\n\n<p>do you know any tracker items or anything where I can find the problems with this function?</p>', '2012-05-04 16:15:39'),
(5646037, 204, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed via Eclipse. </p>', '2012-05-11 08:24:46'),
(5656258, 205, 'mbabker', '<p>PHP in most instances is able to handle paths with either type of and both slashes in it.</p>', '2012-05-11 17:24:22'),
(5668633, 124, 'gpongelli', '<p>Good pull request, hope will be merged soon.<br>\nLet me know, so I can update my PostgreSQL pull.</p>\n\n<p>Eng. Gabriele Pongelli</p>', '2012-05-12 13:54:28'),
(5682710, 168, 'aaronschmitz', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28525">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28525</a></p>', '2012-05-14 05:00:51'),
(5743295, 153, 'azrul', '<p>The problem is real and does need fixing, but the commit is actually bad, and I am pretty strongly against merging this into the core.</p>', '2012-05-16 15:10:42'),
(5753793, 210, 'elinw', '<p>You don''t want to totally remove permissions from the component since those provide the fall backs that are used in absence of specific settings.  Ideally you only use the item level ones in special cases, similar to the article level permissions in content.</p>', '2012-05-16 22:25:48'),
(5758856, 210, 'infograf768', '<p>Also, please add a Feature Tracker on joomlacode an reference back here:<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8549">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8549</a></p>\n\n<p>Forgot:<br>\nYou are deleting in this patch a new string just committed:<br>\nCOM_MENUS_ITEM_FIELD_HIDE_UNASSIGNED="Hide Unassigned Modules"</p>', '2012-05-17 06:04:42'),
(5759814, 153, 'piotr-cz', '<p>There is another commit for the issule: <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1209" class="issue-link" title="Updated database session code to avoid duplication of session id">joomla/joomla-platform#1209</a></p>', '2012-05-17 07:51:12'),
(5762624, 153, 'elinw', '<p>Jonah and Azrul could you comment on #1209 as an alternative solution? </p>', '2012-05-17 11:57:47'),
(5764724, 210, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>I didn''t remove the component permissions. I just moved them to the access.xml file along with the menu type and menu item permissions. Also, I see now in this patch that I didn''t use the newest files when I made my changes. I''ll close this request, fix it, create a feature tracker and then submit a new pull request. Thanks!</p>', '2012-05-17 14:11:09'),
(5768715, 210, 'elinw', '<p>You shouldn''t need to move the access.xml from where it was.</p>', '2012-05-17 17:08:10'),
(5770051, 210, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>When I started, com_menus didn''t have an access.xml. I created it and then moved the component permissions to the new access.xml from config.xml so it would look more like com_content. Looking at the commit, I don''t think the access.xml I created got added. Sorry for the confusion, I''m a bit new to Git.</p>', '2012-05-17 18:04:14'),
(5801359, 210, 'elinw', '<p>Oh I see it was just using the default.</p>', '2012-05-19 12:27:34'),
(5821509, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>already a month away.. hope somebody have the solution..</p>', '2012-05-21 12:46:54'),
(5827061, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28552">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28552</a></p>', '2012-05-21 16:30:38'),
(5827713, 212, 'realityking', '<p>Haven''t tested it yet but the idea is awesome!</p>\n\n<p>Note: We''ll have to update the sample data after this has landed.</p>', '2012-05-21 16:56:26'),
(5832394, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>I forgot something else. In order to install properly, in installation/sql/mysql/joomla.sql this line:</p>\n\n<p>INSERT INTO <code>#__menu_types</code> VALUES (1, ''mainmenu'', ''Main Menu'', ''The main menu for the site'');</p>\n\n<p>should be:</p>\n\n<p>INSERT INTO <code>#__menu_types</code> VALUES (1, 0, ''mainmenu'', ''Main Menu'', ''The main menu for the site'');</p>\n\n<p>How do I add this to the pull request? Or should I make a new one?</p>', '2012-05-21 20:09:08'),
(5832516, 212, 'realityking', '<p>You can just add another commit to your branch, it will automatically be part of the pull request.</p>\n\n<p>Another note that just occured to me: We probably need a migration script for this. I''m pretty sure something weird will happen if there isn''t an entry in the asset table for a menu or menu item.</p>', '2012-05-21 20:13:48'),
(5832685, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>Thanks for the help.</p>\n\n<p>Regarding the migration script, when I was working on this, I started by just doing ALTER TABLE to add the asset_id column. Everything defaulted to 0 asset_id and nothing blew up. That might be enough.</p>', '2012-05-21 20:21:56'),
(5841433, 212, 'infograf768', '<p>Created an update sql file containing<br>\nALTER TABLE  <code>#__menu_types</code> ADD COLUMN <code>asset_id</code> INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT ''0'' COMMENT ''FK to the #__assets table.'' AFTER <code>id</code>;<br>\nALTER TABLE  <code>#__menu</code> ADD COLUMN <code>asset_id</code> INTEGER UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT ''0'' COMMENT ''FK to the #__assets table.'' AFTER <code>id</code>;</p>\n\n<p>Ran it and then tested on existing site</p>\n\n<p>saw some errors preventing the tmpl from displaying wen editing a menu item</p>\n\n<p>$canDo      = $this-&gt;canDo;  // error<br>\n$canDoAlso  = $this-&gt;canDoAlso;  //error</p>\n\n<p>Also some errors with divs in views/item/tmpl/edit.php</p>', '2012-05-22 07:57:18'),
(5850636, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>Alright, this latest commit should fix the problems that infograf768 saw.</p>', '2012-05-22 15:49:10'),
(5866055, 212, 'infograf768', '<p>The above errors are now corrected.<br>\n<a href="https://github.com/test" class="user-mention">@test</a><br>\nDefault Administrator has no access to menus/menu items permissions.</p>', '2012-05-23 06:28:14'),
(5879553, 213, 'infograf768', '<p>Tracker is: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28561">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28561</a><br>\nneeds one more tester</p>', '2012-05-23 17:33:57'),
(5882408, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>I fixed the permissions for new installations. For current installations you need to execute:</p>\n\n<p>UPDATE #__assets SET rules = ''{"core.admin":{"7":1},"core.manage":{"6":1},"core.create":{"3":1},"core.delete":[],"core.edit":{"4":1},"core.edit.state":{"5":1},"core.edit.own":[]}'' WHERE id = 16;</p>', '2012-05-23 19:34:39'),
(5892088, 212, 'infograf768', '<p>@ test<br>\nThis does not work here.</p>', '2012-05-24 05:24:17'),
(5892272, 214, 'infograf768', '<p>Please add a tracker in the Joomla Feature Tracker on joomlacode ( <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8549">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8549</a> )<br>\nAlso, this pull is so incomplete that it cannot be tested. </p>', '2012-05-24 05:30:15'),
(5893143, 214, 'Twentronix', '<p>I''ve added some changes and options. It''s working fine and in my opinion it''s ready for a pull right now. Also added a tracker: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28565">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28565</a>. Please advice.</p>', '2012-05-24 05:48:55'),
(5894373, 214, 'Twentronix', '<p>Test instructions (J!2.5)</p>\n\n<p>1- Overwrite your J2.5 files:<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/214/files">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/214/files</a><br>\n2- Go to article manager in back-end Joomla. <br>\n3- Options -&gt; Integration -&gt; JGLOBAL_FEED_SHOW_READMORE_LABEL: Show<br>\n4- Add some articles, split them with readmore. Create menu-item of type<br>\ncategory. Maybe you need to use the syndication module to get the RSS feed<br>\nlink.<br>\n5- Go to your RSS feed for that category with Firefox:<br>\nview-source:<a href="http://your-rss-feed.com">http://your-rss-feed.com</a><br>\n6- Now you can see the read more links in the descriptions. You can turn them<br>\noff with step 3.</p>', '2012-05-24 07:27:41'),
(5895363, 214, 'infograf768', '<p>Corrected your patch. See joomlacode tracker. As I commented there, I see no use for the Read More.</p>', '2012-05-24 08:41:34'),
(5915048, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>The only thing I can think of is that maybe the group and/or asset ids are different on your dataset.</p>', '2012-05-24 19:15:11'),
(5924437, 212, 'infograf768', '<p>I am using default trunk install with sampledata, patched with your diff and both queries.<br>\nI suggest you test this environment</p>', '2012-05-25 06:54:07'),
(5924801, 198, 'piotr-cz', '<p>cool, thanks!</p>', '2012-05-25 07:28:06'),
(5924852, 205, 'piotr-cz', '<p><a href="https://github.com/pietjepel" class="user-mention">@pietjepel</a> What value did you put into $live_site param?</p>', '2012-05-25 07:32:28'),
(5971089, 174, 'marcusds', '<p>Why is this still not fixed? Major pain.</p>', '2012-05-28 19:53:52'),
(5974668, 174, 'mbabker', '<p>This should be fixed in the current code as it appears to have been committed after 2.5.4''s release.  So, it should be included in 2.5.5.  If you are testing the current development code and it isn''t fixed, please submit a new issue.</p>', '2012-05-29 02:13:53'),
(5994006, 195, 'Balleno', '<p>I have found the source of the problem.<br>\nIt was in a custom list field with the following line:<br>\n$query = new JDatabaseQuery;<br>\nThe "new JDatabaseQuery" is probably not supported any more in 2.5,<br>\nso it only works with the following:<br>\n$query = $db-&gt;getQuery(true); - where $db id the database object.</p>', '2012-05-29 19:56:58'),
(6026837, 218, 'jlleblanc', '<p>Also, a jQuery integration plan has been added here: <a href="http://docs.joomla.org/JavaScript_Working_Group#jQuery_Integration_Plan">http://docs.joomla.org/JavaScript_Working_Group#jQuery_Integration_Plan</a></p>', '2012-05-31 02:58:19'),
(6028508, 216, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a new tracker on joomlacode. Add testing instructions. Cross-reference here. </p>', '2012-05-31 05:49:40'),
(6028511, 217, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a new tracker on joomlacode. Add testing instructions. Cross-reference here. </p>', '2012-05-31 05:50:02'),
(6028555, 218, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a Joomla Feature tracker in <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8549">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8549</a> and reference here.</p>', '2012-05-31 05:54:31'),
(6034251, 218, 'laoneo', '<p>Can''t wait till jQuery will be available in joomla core!! The folk of the G4J project will thank you...I think jQuery.noConflict(); should be in a separate file. Users which care abut site speed do have a javascript minifier like jFinalizer installed anyway which packs all javascript files into one....</p>', '2012-05-31 12:15:37'),
(6034338, 219, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker on joomlacode and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-05-31 12:20:22'),
(6034419, 217, 'krileon', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28591">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28591</a></p>', '2012-05-31 12:25:22'),
(6034431, 216, 'krileon', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28591">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28591</a></p>', '2012-05-31 12:25:44'),
(6035132, 219, 'laoneo', '<p>Here it is <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28592">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=28592</a></p>', '2012-05-31 13:03:14'),
(6036398, 212, 'sanderpotjer', '<p><a href="https://github.com/rmcdaniel" class="user-mention">@rmcdaniel</a> great idea to add ACL support to menu''s! Much requested feature among the users of Joomla ACL.</p>\n\n<p>Just started testing this new feature, and during the installation of fresh site with sampledata errors are visible while installing sampledata. The reason for this is that for example "installation/sql/mysql/sample_data.sq" should be updates as well with asset_id values for the #__menu and #__menu_types. Same for any other sample data file. In addition to this there should be references for all menu items and menus in the #__assets table as well.</p>', '2012-05-31 13:54:52'),
(6036829, 212, 'infograf768', '<p><a href="https://github.com/sanderpotjer" class="user-mention">@sanderpotjer</a><br>\nIndeed. This is what I tried to convey above. If we want to implemnt this for 3.x, we will not only have to change sampledatas, but also provide a migration for existing sites.</p>', '2012-05-31 14:12:25'),
(6036987, 218, 'jlleblanc', '<p>Feature Tracker item created: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28593">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28593</a></p>', '2012-05-31 14:17:57'),
(6036995, 218, 'gnomeontherun', '<p>I recommend adding jQuery.noConflict(); to the end of the jQuery file.</p>', '2012-05-31 14:18:17'),
(6037373, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>Thanks for the information. I''ll try to get the sample data and the assets done today. As for the migration script, can you give me any ideas on how to start? Is there an example in the installation folder already? Any documentation? Another thing that someone with more experience could look at is how I implemented _getAssetParentId(). I think it might be supposed to return the menutype id, or maybe it should return the parent menu item if that exists?</p>', '2012-05-31 14:31:10'),
(6037583, 212, 'infograf768', '<p>We do not have any migration script in present trunk. Just some simple updates to the db in com_admin.</p>', '2012-05-31 14:39:26'),
(6037980, 218, 'kyleledbetter', '<p>Not sure if this question or request belongs here, but should we also offer a toggle to use a CDN/hosted version of jQuery in the core? Thx for working on this btw</p>', '2012-05-31 14:54:47'),
(6042956, 212, 'sanderpotjer', '<p>Actually, the core.edit.own action is not needed in this component at the moment. There is no information stored in the menu tables about the creators of menutypes/menus. So it is better to remove the entire core.edit.own action for this component or we need to extend the menu tables with the creator information. </p>', '2012-05-31 18:00:28'),
(6043236, 212, 'rmcdaniel', '<p>Does that mean I should remove it from the menu section as well?</p>', '2012-05-31 18:11:32'),
(6043328, 212, 'sanderpotjer', '<p><a href="https://github.com/rmcdaniel" class="user-mention">@rmcdaniel</a> yes that is correct to remove core.edit.own from the menu section as well. Sorry for the confusing btw, just noticed edit.own isn''t possible at the moment, so better to remove it for now.</p>', '2012-05-31 18:15:18'),
(6043603, 212, 'sanderpotjer', '<p>Another thing I noticed, when installing new components an entry in the #__menu table is created for each of the backend menu items of the component (this is currently default in Joomla). Now with this new menu ACL an entry in the assets table is created as well, but missing the correct parent and level id''s. This is more difficult to fix because there is no ''menutype'' for the backend menu items. </p>\n\n<p>This might be solved if the backend menu will be transformed in a similar system as the frontend menus. I know there are plans for that, but don''t know the status of that. So need to look into this (but want to share it already).</p>', '2012-05-31 18:25:31'),
(6045768, 218, 'jlleblanc', '<p><a href="https://github.com/kyleledbetter" class="user-mention">@kyleledbetter</a> yup, that''s part of what I''m asking. I know we''re loathe to add more options in the configuration.php file and a plugin seems overweight. I''m wondering if we might want to introduce an "extended" configuration panel for Joomla 3.0 that isn''t tied to configuration.php and would allow for later-breaking features like this.</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/gnomeontherun" class="user-mention">@gnomeontherun</a> I lean towards appending <code>jQuery.noConflict();</code> directly to the file as well. Some people brought up the fact that this adds One More Thing To Remember To Do whenever a new version of jQuery comes out, which is a valid concern.</p>', '2012-05-31 19:54:23'),
(6045835, 218, 'gnomeontherun', '<p><a href="https://github.com/jlleblanc" class="user-mention">@jlleblanc</a> valid concern, but also something that could be automated during the build process.</p>', '2012-05-31 19:57:24'),
(6046673, 218, 'beat', '<p>Hi all,<br>\nFor reference here is my pull request which might be reviewed with "new eyes" now that jQuery inclusion has been decided:<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/736" class="issue-link" title="Adding ''behavior.jquery'' to Joomla Framework with deep non-conflict mode and support for concurrent jQuery versions running">joomla/joomla-platform#736</a></p>\n\n<p>For pre- and post- javascript files inclusions javascript code (required for CDN downloading of jquery) you can take a look at the proposed patches for the 2 files:<br>\nlibraries/joomla/document/document.php<br>\nlibraries/joomla/document/html/renderer/head.php</p>\n\n<p>here:</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/736/files">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/736/files</a></p>\n\n<p>Pretty easy to do and would do that job and solve many other valid uses of defining JS variables before including JS files...</p>\n\n<p>I''m still to avoid changing imported libraries, and above solution is clean, elegant and same inclusion if from joomla install (which should be default for security reasons) or from a CDN.</p>\n\n<p>Finally, changes to file:<br>\nlibraries/joomla/html/html/behavior.php<br>\non that page allow to solve all the dependencies of jQuery plugins, and at same time of jquery versioning.</p>\n\n<p>Let me know what you think, and if there are parts that you think are not useful.</p>', '2012-05-31 20:33:20'),
(6049680, 220, 'sanderpotjer', '<p>JoomlaCode: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28595">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28595</a></p>', '2012-05-31 22:53:19'),
(6051229, 218, 'jlleblanc', '<p><a href="https://github.com/beat" class="user-mention">@beat</a> ah, yes, I''d forgotten that the CDN was one of the reasons appending noConflict to the end was a non-starter.</p>', '2012-06-01 00:41:34'),
(6059532, 166, 'JoaoSRaposo', '<p>Hello gpongelli,</p>\n\n<p>Really nice work. <br>\nPostgres support is very important to easily integrate Joomla with other applications that are using postgres DB.</p>\n\n<p>Thank you very much for you work and hope this pull request will be included in next Joomla release.</p>', '2012-06-01 12:43:53'),
(6060083, 124, 'realityking', '<p>I think this has already been committed. Please confirm &amp; close. Thanks.</p>', '2012-06-01 13:16:02'),
(6060093, 218, 'DaveOzric', '<p>This would be simply awesome!</p>', '2012-06-01 13:16:28'),
(6060219, 124, 'mbabker', '<p>It''s been committed.</p>', '2012-06-01 13:23:30'),
(6068090, 153, 'realityking', '<p>Shouldn''t we rather try to make sure that every key is unique? Or is there a reason why we can''t guarantee that?</p>', '2012-06-01 18:55:08'),
(6068093, 153, 'realityking', '<p>Shouldn''t we rather try to make sure that every key is unique? Or is there a reason why we can''t guarantee that?</p>', '2012-06-01 18:55:10'),
(6068186, 208, 'realityking', '<p>Could you open an issue on the tracker for this? Thanks.</p>', '2012-06-01 18:58:47'),
(6068567, 208, 'amh-mw', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28604">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28604</a></p>', '2012-06-01 19:16:16'),
(6072882, 153, 'elinw', '<p>That''s the approach of #1209</p>', '2012-06-01 23:20:35'),
(6072987, 212, 'elinw', '<p>In what sense is there ownership in menus?<br>\nthe edit.own  management is very messy to start out with since it violates a number of principles of ACL. There were very good reasons it was decided not to implement it below the category level for anything but articles in 1.6+.  </p>\n\n<p>You need to look at com_categories as that is the only core component that has a table extending jtablenested. That should show you how to work with nesting correctly.</p>', '2012-06-01 23:29:44'),
(6073591, 208, 'elinw', '<p>Wouldn''t it be better to move these to the cms folder than to have a cms specific modification in the joomla folder?</p>', '2012-06-02 00:30:43'),
(6075274, 213, 'elinw', '<p>I think this should be 2.5 not 1.6. It''s changing history to call it 1.6.</p>', '2012-06-02 06:18:50'),
(6075740, 213, 'realityking', '<p>All of these classes and methods were also present in 1.6.0 so I felt this to be more accurate.</p>', '2012-06-02 08:07:20'),
(6075798, 208, 'realityking', '<p>The fix isn''t so much CMS specific than already fixed in the platform. Just in a different way we probably don''t wanna do for 2.5.x (these classes are now autoloadable in the platform)</p>', '2012-06-02 08:17:49'),
(6076708, 221, 'sanderpotjer', '<p>JoomlaCode: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28610">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28610</a></p>', '2012-06-02 11:16:07'),
(6079126, 144, 'gnomeontherun', '<p>Just FYI, my proposed work with the admin menu will end up removing this. It uses the same concepts as the frontend menu for the most part.</p>', '2012-06-02 17:11:25'),
(6079427, 190, 'elinw', '<p>The reason you allow for no terms is because you mght be using the filters and no terms at all.</p>\n\n<p>Is this good to go? have people tested it? If so will you please report on the tracker so we can make it rtc or if not can we make it not pending anymore?</p>', '2012-06-02 17:51:09'),
(6079786, 208, 'elinw', '<p>That''s what I''m saying I think. Rather than modify the CMS version of the platform why don''t we add to  cms? I think we should try to keep thing as clean as possible.</p>', '2012-06-02 18:45:34'),
(6080765, 208, 'realityking', '<p>Define clean? If you mean 11.4 - well than I should probably not backport all that stuff from the platform ;)</p>\n\n<p>Seriously there''s no harm in adding this. Yes it will be overwritten by the next full platform sync, but that''s fine because it''s a better - and fully compatible - fix.</p>', '2012-06-02 21:13:09'),
(6100238, 208, 'amh-mw', '<p>If it helps clarify this patch,</p>\n\n<p>libraries/joomla/access/access.php<br>\n13  +jimport(''joomla.application.component.helper'');</p>\n\n<p>fixes the JComponentHelper dependencies found in the same file at</p>\n\n<p>288 $result = array(JComponentHelper::getParams(''com_users'')-&gt;get(''guest_usergroup'',<br>\n1));<br>\n301 $query-&gt;where(''a.id = '' . (int)<br>\nJComponentHelper::getParams(''com_users'')-&gt;get(''guest_usergroup'', 1));</p>\n\n<p>and</p>\n\n<p>libraries/joomla/installer/installer.php<br>\n17  +jimport(''joomla.event.dispatcher'');</p>\n\n<p>fixes the JDispatcher dependencies found in the same file at</p>\n\n<p>466 $dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();<br>\n544 $dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();<br>\n658 $dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();<br>\n710 $dispatcher = JDispatcher::getInstance();</p>', '2012-06-04 14:31:25'),
(6116477, 218, 'jlleblanc', '<p>I''ve now added updates for "post scripts" to be added immediately after linked scripts. I''ve also added the possibility of using a CDN URL in place of a local copy of jQuery.</p>', '2012-06-05 02:43:36'),
(6117915, 190, 'fititnt', '<p><a href="https://github.com/elinw" class="user-mention">@elinw</a> for me still ok from my last commit on this pull. But before do a merge, need confirmation that more people tested it just to be sure.</p>\n\n<p>Also, if someone think that have a better way to do it, I can work a bit more on this pull. I will just avoid big changes before 3.0. I have a few ideas but they change com_finder parameters on administrator and could break layouts, so are not a good idea for Joomla 2.5 LTS and still better at least do in a different pull.</p>', '2012-06-05 05:37:25'),
(6144463, 181, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p><a href="https://github.com/elinw" class="user-mention">@elinw</a> </p>\n\n<p>I seem to have worked this out. It looks like it was something to do with my company''s network after all. I don''t understand it but at least I have a solution.</p>\n\n<p>Now, to post a report (and I have several) I need to associate it with a ''project''? There are heaps of projects on joomlacode, most of them look like 3rd party plugins. Is there a project just for com_media or would this be considered as part of some core Joomla project? I also have things to post about CodeMirror, what project would that be listed as?</p>', '2012-06-06 07:18:09'),
(6149916, 181, 'mbabker', '<p>This will link you right to the CMS Bug Tracker: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8103">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&amp;tracker_id=8103</a></p>', '2012-06-06 13:01:19'),
(6158000, 230, 'spignataro', '<p>Tracker issue posted: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28626">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28626</a></p>\n\n<p>Although I am not sure why it looks like it is in the wrong spot.</p>\n\n<p>Kindest regards,</p>\n\n<p>--Steven Pignataro</p>', '2012-06-06 18:07:23'),
