(6180259, 181, 'elinw', '<p>No don''t do a project, you want this to be part of the core Joomla cms<br>\nproject.</p>\n\n<p>Elin</p>\n\n<p>On Wed, Jun 6, 2012 at 3:18 AM, Elijah Madden &lt;<br><a href="mailto:reply@reply.github.com">reply@reply.github.com</a></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>wrote:</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/elinw" class="user-mention">@elinw</a></p>\n\n<p>I seem to have worked this out. It looks like it was something to do with<br>\nmy company''s network after all. I don''t understand it but at least I have a<br>\nsolution.</p>\n\n<p>Now, to post a report (and I have several) I need to associate it with a<br>\n''project''? There are heaps of projects on joomlacode, most of them look<br>\nlike 3rd party plugins. Is there a project just for com_media or would this<br>\nbe considered as part of some core Joomla project? I also have things to<br>\npost about CodeMirror, what project would that be listed as?</p>\n\n<hr>\n<p>Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/181#issuecomment-6144463" class="issue-link" title="com_media improvements">joomla/joomla-cms#181</a></p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-06-07 16:14:16'),
