(6987372, 272, 'realityking', '<p>Since the code has made its way to the CMS with the platform merge I''m closing this one.</p>\n\n<p>I plan to put this back in some way (either just for progressive or a new cache mode), I''d love to hear your thoughts on that.</p>', '2012-07-14 22:55:28'),
(7033138, 280, 'phproberto', '<p>I forgot to remove CSS that disables selects :)</p>', '2012-07-17 11:56:58'),
(7036261, 279, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker on joomlacode, reference here and explain the issue with testing instructions.</p>', '2012-07-17 14:15:12'),
(7036426, 280, 'infograf768', '<p>Needs testing first. Reports on joomlacode tracker.</p>', '2012-07-17 14:20:22'),
(7036558, 279, 'willdurand', '<p>Seriously?</p>', '2012-07-17 14:24:52'),
(7037184, 280, 'realityking', '<p>3 things:<br>\n-Someone needs to make sure this has no negative effect on accessibility<br>\n-The comment explicit says this is used due to an IE issue. That means we need testing as far back as IE7 (2.5) or IE8 (3.0)<br>\n-All those files belong to the platform so it has to be submitted there as well.</p>', '2012-07-17 14:45:10'),
(7037409, 279, 'lolautruche', '<p>Openness fail</p>', '2012-07-17 14:51:14'),
(7037412, 279, 'clawfire', '<p>"please user 45 differents tools before submiting some fix to our apps, ''cause time wasted to patch our code is not enough. Cheers" #sarcasm</p>', '2012-07-17 14:51:17'),
(7037478, 279, 'bdunogier', '<p>I''m not a Joomla expert, but testing this might prove a tad difficult...</p>', '2012-07-17 14:53:04'),
(7037878, 279, 'elinw', '<p>I don''t what it has to do with openness since the process and the fact that the tracker not git hub is the point of truth for issues is documented in a million places.  The way you test manually is to apply it and make sure that nothing changes, which obviously will be true in this case since this is just a code quality fix. Also the pull would need to be revised since it includes a platform change unless you''ve sent that change already to the platform repo.</p>', '2012-07-17 15:04:16'),
(7037923, 279, 'Rydgel', '<p>PHP.</p>', '2012-07-17 15:05:22'),
(7037957, 279, 'gries', '<p>I would say that THIS is the right case to choose pragmatism over process...</p>', '2012-07-17 15:06:51'),
(7038235, 279, 'digitalkaoz', '<p>rly? lol!</p>', '2012-07-17 15:15:46'),
(7038435, 279, 'realityking', '<p>It would be really helpful if you could submit the fix for libraries/joomla/database/driver/pdo.php to joomla/joomla-platform. We treat the platform like an upstream library and we''ll pick up the fix with the next merge. The platform accepts pull requests BTW ;)</p>', '2012-07-17 15:20:50'),
(7039428, 279, 'pborreli', '<p><a href="https://github.com/realityking" class="user-mention">@realityking</a> done in <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1378" class="issue-link" title="Remove unreachable code (dead code)">joomla/joomla-platform#1378</a></p>', '2012-07-17 15:49:56'),
(7039532, 279, 'realityking', '<p><a href="https://github.com/pborreli" class="user-mention">@pborreli</a> <br>\nThanks. I added tiny comment, just waiting for the unit tests to pass (<a href="http://developer.joomla.org/pulls/">http://developer.joomla.org/pulls/</a>) and I''ll merge it.</p>', '2012-07-17 15:53:18'),
(7040906, 280, 'phproberto', '<p>The IE issue was a valuable information to share. That wasn''t here or in joomlacode :(</p>\n\n<p>Do you have a link with the issue reported with IE?</p>\n\n<p>I have tested it on Joomla 3.0 + IE8 ( <a href="http://i50.tinypic.com/2zhnuo7.png">http://i50.tinypic.com/2zhnuo7.png</a> ). Actually I haven''t a VM with IE7. Can you test it?</p>\n\n<p>Tested: </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>tabs skip disabled selects</li>\n<li>selects remain unclickable</li>\n<li>selects keep overlayed</li>\n</ul><p>I have no problem to submit it to platform after fully testing.</p>', '2012-07-17 16:35:30'),
(7041119, 280, 'realityking', '<p>Yeah sorry about that, I just noticed the comment when I looked at your patch. The comment was already present in digitarald.de''s original code so I have no isight why it was added. It might have been related to just IE6.</p>', '2012-07-17 16:42:19'),
(7073433, 280, 'phproberto', '<p>Also tested and working on IE7 &amp; Joomla 2.5.6 :</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://i50.tinypic.com/5mkg07.png">http://i50.tinypic.com/5mkg07.png</a></p>\n\n<p>Probably was related to IE6. Happy to read that :)</p>', '2012-07-18 16:12:00'),
(7099425, 265, 'elinw', '<p>Superceded by #284</p>', '2012-07-19 14:21:00'),
(7104506, 283, 'realityking', '<p>Good catch!</p>\n\n<p>Since this is a platform issue could you please submit it here: <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform</a></p>\n\n<p>Also please replace the use of JRequest with JInput or we won''t be able to merge it.</p>\n\n<p>Jus the platform pull will be fine, we''ll merge the platform back into the CMS soon.</p>', '2012-07-19 17:11:34'),
(7107422, 283, 'Bakual', '<p>PR added on platform: <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1389" class="issue-link" title="JFactory::createDocument always creates HTML documents.">joomla/joomla-platform#1389</a></p>\n\n<p>I guess we can close this one here then?</p>', '2012-07-19 18:50:45'),
(7107522, 283, 'realityking', '<p>Yes this can be closed. Thank you.</p>', '2012-07-19 18:53:27'),
(7125005, 285, 'infograf768', '<p>Please add a tracker on joomlacode and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-07-20 08:29:51'),
(7126151, 285, 'upsj', '<p>Sorry, I''m not familiar with the joomla issue tracking system. I''ve added a tracker (#28849)</p>', '2012-07-20 09:34:06'),
(7133097, 286, 'realityking', '<p>Thanks. Committed manually.</p>', '2012-07-20 15:29:18'),
(7142200, 287, 'mbabker', '<p>Curious as to why you''ve got the sample_*.sql files now recreating the tables.  Also, do you have an update SQL for the schema changes that are being made?</p>', '2012-07-20 21:30:15'),
(7142342, 287, 'elinw', '<p>See <br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28854">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28854</a></p>', '2012-07-20 21:37:10'),
(7143314, 287, 'elinw', '<p>Will do the schema changes and updates next, but I''d be happy to have<br>\npeople do some testing as is and confirm it''s good. Although I"m happy to<br>\nshare the updates that I''ve done.</p>\n\n<p>About recreating the tables if they don''t exist ... two things.<br>\n1. sometimes people may have messed with their core tables.<br>\n2. We have a goal of letting people reset their site and install a new set<br>\nof sample data.</p>\n\n<p>ALTER TABLE <code>#__contact_details</code> DROP <code>imagepos</code>;<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__content</code> DROP <code>title_alias</code>, DROP <code>sectionid</code>, DROP <code>mask</code>,<br>\nDROP <code>parentid</code>;<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__newsfeeds</code> DROP <code>filename</code>;<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__weblinks</code> DROP <code>sid</code>, DROP <code>date</code>, DROP <code>archived</code>, DROP<br><code>approved</code>;<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__menu</code> DROP <code>ordering</code>;</p>\n\n<p>ALTER TABLE <code>#__weblinks</code>   ADD   <code>version</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''1'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__weblinks</code>   ADD   <code>images</code> text NOT NULL;</p>\n\n<p>ALTER TABLE <code>#__newsfeeds</code>  ADD    <code>description</code> text NOT NULL;<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__newsfeeds</code>   ADD   <code>version</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''1'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__newsfeeds</code>   ADD   <code>hits</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL DEFAULT<br>\n''0'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__newsfeeds</code>   ADD   <code>images</code> text NOT NULL;</p>\n\n<p>ALTER TABLE <code>#__contact_details</code>   ADD   <code>version</code> int(10) unsigned NOT<br>\nNULL DEFAULT ''1'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__contact_details</code>   ADD   <code>hits</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''0'';</p>\n\n<p>ALTER TABLE <code>#__banners</code>  ADD      <code>created_by</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''0'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__banners</code>  ADD     <code>created_by_alias</code> varchar(255) NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT '''';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__banners</code>  ADD     <code>modified</code> datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT<br>\n''0000-00-00 00:00:00'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__banners</code>  ADD     <code>modified_by</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''0'';<br>\nALTER TABLE <code>#__banners</code>   ADD   <code>version</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''1'';</p>\n\n<p>ALTER TABLE <code>#__categories</code>   ADD   <code>version</code> int(10) unsigned NOT NULL<br>\nDEFAULT ''1'';</p>\n\n<p>On Fri, Jul 20, 2012 at 5:30 PM, Michael Babker &lt;<br><a href="mailto:reply@reply.github.com">reply@reply.github.com</a></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>wrote:</p>\n\n<p>Curious as to why you''ve got the sample_*.sql files now recreating the<br>\ntables.  Also, do you have an update SQL for the schema changes that are<br>\nbeing made?</p>\n\n<hr>\n<p>Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/287#issuecomment-7142200" class="issue-link" title="Clean up SQL files including deleting unused fields and updating sample data">joomla/joomla-cms#287</a></p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-07-20 22:30:43'),
(7143491, 287, 'elinw', '<p>Why not now ..</p>', '2012-07-20 22:39:39'),
(7144078, 287, 'realityking', '<p>I''m not a big fan of adding table fields that are not set up in code. Could we do that in two steps? I''m afraid we might end up with more orphan fields that way.</p>', '2012-07-20 23:12:00'),
(7149420, 287, 'elinw', '<p>No we''re not going to and it is extremely wrong on many levels to do complex sql fixes and code same time, at least more than one or two lines. As much as possible we should try to isolate changes.  This is a very complex commit as it is.  I  promise if we don''t get other changes to standardize the code in we can go back and take them out.  There is no way ever to move forward if you are not willing to take the first step.   </p>', '2012-07-21 02:52:07'),
(7149443, 284, 'elinw', '<p>This is one of the few cases where fixing the sql at the same time as repairing the code makes sense. That is only because it is a very specific line and it''s not possible to test the change without making the sql change.</p>', '2012-07-21 02:55:22'),
(7150334, 74, 'elinw', '<p>This was fixed..</p>', '2012-07-21 05:56:07'),
(7150345, 276, 'elinw', '<p>Dennis is there a reason you didn''t just submit a pull request to fix?</p>', '2012-07-21 05:58:00'),
(7159442, 288, 'infograf768', '<p>The "view" is not translated in default Joomla.<br><strong>Articles</strong> Â» ??Article?? Â» <strong>Single Article</strong></p>\n\n<p>This means new language strings:<br>\nOn a default sample data core install:</p>\n\n<p>ARCHIVE="Archive"<br>\nARTICLE="Article"<br>\nCATEGORY="Category"<br>\nCOM_FINDER_MENU_SEARCH_VIEW_TITLE="FINDER MENU SEARCH VIEW TITLE"<br>\nCOM_NEWSFEEDS_CATEGORY_GROUP_LABEL="NEWSFEEDS CATEGORY GROUP LABEL"<br>\nCONTACT="Contact"<br>\nFORM="Form"<br>\nFRONTPAGE="Frontpage"<br>\nLOGIN="Login"<br>\nNEWSFEEDS_NEWSFEED_INDIVIDUAL_FEED_LABEL="NEWSFEED INDIVIDUAL FEED LABEL"<br>\nPROFILE="Profile"<br>\nREGISTRATION="Registration"<br>\nREMIND="Remind"<br>\nRESET="Reset"<br>\nSEARCH="Search"</p>\n\n<p>Also, it breaks the manager display when the "view" text is too long.<br>\nIf we implement this, we should only for 3.0 as this would require new constants in all metadata.xml + new strings.</p>\n\n<p>Please open a tracker on joomlacode and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-07-22 07:42:43'),
(7161281, 288, 'Bakual', '<p>Aww, didn''t notice that. And there I was thinking it would be a simple and easy change.</p>\n\n<p>Would that go into the feature tracker or into the bug tracker?</p>\n\n<p>Another approach would be to either show the view title or the layout title. Taking the view title as fallback for the layout. This way the text shouldn''t get to long and break the manager display. I would prefer to show the view always like it was in Joomla 1.5 but I think both ways would work.</p>\n\n<p>Currently it just makes no sense to have a title in metadata.xml at all. It gets checked in menumanager but isn''t used for anything. Either make it completely optional or use the info somewhere :-)</p>', '2012-07-22 12:39:54'),
(7165676, 288, 'Bakual', '<ul>\n<li>Made the title in the metadata.xml optional. Only showing it when it''s set.</li>\n<li>Deleted the title and message from the view metadata.xml in the core where they were not translated.</li>\n</ul><p>This way nothing should change for the core, but an extension developer can decide to show the viewname in the menumanager by setting it in the metadata.xml.<br>\nI guess this makes most sense.</p>', '2012-07-22 21:10:25'),
(7168608, 287, 'elinw', '<p>See #290 if you are worried about unused fields. :P</p>', '2012-07-23 04:05:21'),
(7170237, 288, 'Bakual', '<p>Trackitem on Feature Tracker:<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28860">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28860</a></p>', '2012-07-23 06:05:09'),
(7178762, 291, 'realityking', '<p>I committed the DS part directly. Do we need the item-form change? Is something broken?</p>', '2012-07-23 14:07:44'),
(7178915, 291, 'Bakual', '<p>The "item-form" breaks the buttons, you can''t save or cancel the form.<br>\nIt''s also noted in the <a href="http://docs.joomla.org/Potential_backward_compatibility_issues_in_Joomla_3.0_and_Joomla_Platform_12.1">compatibility issues doc</a> : </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Forms that have name="adminForm" now also require id="adminForm"</p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-07-23 14:13:22'),
(7179336, 291, 'realityking', '<p>Got it, indeed it''s broken. Will take care of it. Thank you!</p>', '2012-07-23 14:28:21'),
(7234811, 292, 'realityking', '<p>Didn''t we just do that? <a href="https://github.com/JTracker/jissues/commit/4d5fb7458c6461d5b6acc7a415d6fb092566bda5" class="commit-link"><tt>4d5fb74</tt></a></p>', '2012-07-24 22:00:15'),
(7234830, 292, 'bradp', '<p>Yet I still saved space and optimized them further without losing quality. Never hurts, right?</p>', '2012-07-24 22:01:18'),
(7250824, 293, 'pjwiseman', '<p>Added three more minor changes.<br>\n1) Images now use versioning parameters to avoid the browser cache flush otherwise needed during testing.  Unfortunately this only works then moving to the branch.  A cache flush is still required following testing to revert.<br>\n2) The Prev/Next/Refresh buttons now look ok in IE9 without the gradient fill.<br>\n3) Slight positioning adjustment to align refresh with the prev/next buttons.<br>\nReady for a final test.  See tracker 26745.</p>', '2012-07-25 14:42:09'),
(7265597, 284, 'elinw', '<p>replaced by #294</p>', '2012-07-25 23:40:32'),
(7267074, 294, 'elinw', '<p>Note that a version of this has also been submitted to the platform with full unit test coverage. We can in the meantime put coverage in the cms repo if we want.</p>', '2012-07-26 01:28:08'),
(7284986, 287, 'elinw', '<p>Close #295</p>', '2012-07-26 17:47:47'),
(7297230, 267, 'phproberto', '<p>I think you are true. Sent a pull request to the platform repo:</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1415" class="issue-link" title="JRegistryFormatINI::stringToObject() preg_match key validation">joomla/joomla-platform#1415</a></p>\n\n<p>If approved I''ll send it also to the joomla-cms</p>', '2012-07-27 04:16:29'),
(7331736, 267, 'eaxs', '<p>Cool, thanks!</p>', '2012-07-28 09:30:56'),
(7350323, 101, 'elkuku', '<p>Added to the book of useless contribution attempts <img class="emoji" title=":disappointed:" alt=":disappointed:" src="https://a248.e.akamai.net/assets.github.com/images/icons/emoji/disappointed.png" height="20" width="20" align="absmiddle"></p>', '2012-07-29 06:53:36'),
(7350330, 122, 'elkuku', '<p>So, this might be closed after six month without attention, or is there anything that is missing ?<br>\nYes I would believe that is currently not mergeable..</p>', '2012-07-29 06:55:51'),
(7352206, 179, 'elinw', '<p>So can everyone answer the following:<br>\nWhat is your error reporting level?<br>\nDo you have debug on?<br>\nIs it only in admin and not in site? <br>\nAlso this is a platform issue so it really should be fixed there.</p>', '2012-07-29 11:53:47'),
(7352641, 179, 'elinw', '<p>Please try changing line 463 to</p>\n\n<pre><code>    $errorReporting = error_reporting();\n    error_reporting(0);\n        usort($a, array(__CLASS__, ''_sortObjects''));\n    error_reporting($errorReporting);\n</code></pre>', '2012-07-29 12:29:50'),
(7354384, 101, 'mbabker', '<p>FWIW, what''s left of this pull that''s not already applied to master - <a href="https://github.com/mbabker/joomla-cms/compare/elkuku_sniff">https://github.com/mbabker/joomla-cms/compare/elkuku_sniff</a></p>', '2012-07-29 16:53:08'),
(7355869, 101, 'elkuku', '<p>Thanks for the heads up, so it wasn''t <em>that</em> useless ;)</p>', '2012-07-29 19:46:11'),
(7403989, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>Hello Elin.. <br>\nWhat is your error reporting level?E_ALL &amp; ~E_NOTICE<br>\nDo you have debug on? yes<br>\nIs it only in admin and not in site? <br>\ncurrently on admin, i see two effect on this, slow joomla that display grid (coz it use jArrayHelper::sortObject() ), Especially on Extension Manager &gt; Manage.</p>\n\n<p>Also on module manager, when i add new.. it mostly display (Serialization of ''SimpleXMLElement'' is not allowed), but sometimes it works</p>\n\n<p>i trace both problem with my zend server:<br>\non Manage Extension, the problem happen on administrator/components/com_installer/model/extension.php (line 76):<br>\nJArrayHelper::sortObjects($result, $this-&gt;getState(''list.ordering''), $this-&gt;getState(''list.direction'') == ''desc'' ? -1 : 1, true, $lang-&gt;getLocale());</p>\n\n<p>on Module Manager, the problem happen on administrator/components/com_modules/models/select.php (line 145):<br>\n$items = JArrayHelper::sortObjects($items, ''name'', 1, true, $lang-&gt;getLocale());</p>\n\n<p>i use ''@'' and also use your method on error_reporting() , the warning dissapear, it fixed module manager, but still it impact Extension Manager &gt; Manage.. coz the temporary solution is only to hide the message instead find the root of the problem.</p>\n\n<p>The problem is not happen on joomla 2.5.3... so it kind a funny how it happen on joomla 2.5.4 and above while the sortObject function is identical.. i think the way the data sent is different...</p>\n\n<p>i show and demo you the problem : <a href="http://youtu.be/__IDvhTHWXQ">http://youtu.be/__IDvhTHWXQ</a></p>\n\n<p>Note: it also happen on a clean joomla install, so definitely not because any component or plugin i installed</p>', '2012-07-31 16:37:22'),
(7406395, 179, 'elinw', '<p>So I think tha we need to do the same thing in each place in the code where usort is used.</p>', '2012-07-31 17:58:28'),
(7408996, 179, 'elkuku', '<p>A hunch:<br>\nCould it be, that an exception is thrown on the way ?</p>\n\n<p>I can reproduce the PHP warning using the code from the PHP bug tracker</p>\n\n<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="o">&lt;?</span><span class="nx">php</span>\n<span class="k">function</span> <span class="nf">cmp</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$a</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nv">$b</span><span class="p">)</span>\n<span class="p">{</span>\n    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$a</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="nv">$b</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>\n        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span>\n    <span class="p">}</span>\n\n    <span class="k">try</span> <span class="p">{</span>\n        <span class="k">throw</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="nx">Exception</span><span class="p">();</span>\n    <span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">catch</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">Exception</span> <span class="nv">$e</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>\n\n    <span class="p">}</span>\n\n    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$a</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="nv">$b</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">?</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">:</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">;</span>\n<span class="p">}</span>\n\n<span class="nv">$a</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="k">array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">6</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">);</span>\n\n<span class="nb">usort</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$a</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"cmp"</span><span class="p">);</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n<p>This results in the mentioned warning on my Linux/PHP 5.3.8 box.</p>\n\n<p>This would also explain why it appears in Joomla! that "suddenly" - Exception were introduced - I don''t remember when..</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/doxadigital" class="user-mention">@doxadigital</a> what a nice bug report <img class="emoji" title=":thumbsup:" alt=":thumbsup:" src="https://a248.e.akamai.net/assets.github.com/images/icons/emoji/thumbsup.png" height="20" width="20" align="absmiddle"> - I wish more people would take the time to record a video of their bugs - Youtube says more than 1k words :P</p>', '2012-07-31 19:32:38'),
(7415200, 179, 'elinw', '<p>It really is a great report. I suspect the reason this may have surfaced is that somewhere we switched something to use an exception instead of an error.</p>', '2012-08-01 00:31:05'),
(7418542, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>maybe we could trace back to 2.5.4 coz that a significant point of what changes that leads to usort() bugs. No problem 2.5.3... i''ve been living with this bug for more than 4 months.. i''m glad that <a href="https://github.com/elinw" class="user-mention">@elinw</a> and <a href="https://github.com/elkuku" class="user-mention">@elkuku</a> join in the discussion... hopefully we can have the solution :D</p>', '2012-08-01 05:15:22'),
(7434569, 179, 'elinw', '<p>I think we need to switch this to a platform discussion. </p>', '2012-08-01 17:52:26'),
(7445960, 179, 'elinw', '<p>Ian suggested changing this line<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/0fc0e90cc0b6e59945bdadcef61c38c388e67c6c/libraries/joomla/utilities/arrayhelper.php#L480">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/0fc0e90cc0b6e59945bdadcef61c38c388e67c6c/libraries/joomla/utilities/arrayhelper.php#L480</a><br>\nso that the arrays are not passed by reference. Can people please test that?</p>', '2012-08-02 02:59:41'),
(7446987, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>Hi elinw.. i just replace the whole arrayhelper.php with the the one you reference and it seem the bug still occur...</p>', '2012-08-02 04:34:55'),
(7449016, 179, 'elinw', '<p>But did you change the one line not to have the  &amp;?</p>', '2012-08-02 07:38:02'),
(7450587, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>do you mean change  </p>\n\n<p>protected static function _sortObjects(&amp;$a, &amp;$b) <br>\nto <br>\nprotected static function _sortObjects($a, $b)..</p>\n\n<p>if yes, than i did... the warning and slow process still occures</p>', '2012-08-02 09:19:28'),
(7455441, 179, 'elinw', '<p>yes ok thanks</p>', '2012-08-02 13:39:35'),
(7457630, 295, 'elinw', '<p>merged</p>', '2012-08-02 14:57:30'),
(7457681, 281, 'elinw', '<p>merged</p>', '2012-08-02 14:58:54'),
(7472368, 179, 'elinw', '<p>I was wondering why the message was on all pages and I guess it is this inthe admin menu module<br>\n$result = JArrayHelper::sortObjects($result, ''text'', 1, true, $lang-&gt;getLocale());</p>\n\n<p>What''s happening on views like article manager and category?</p>', '2012-08-03 00:28:38'),
(7474683, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p>Yes.. its because of administrator/module/mod_menu/helper.php (line 123) that called by default_enabled.php, which is <br>\n$result = JArrayHelper::sortObjects($result, ''text'', 1, true, $lang-&gt;getLocale());</p>\n\n<p>i post some trace result here: <a href="http://www.doxadigital.com/scrape/helperphp.jpg">http://www.doxadigital.com/scrape/helperphp.jpg</a><br>\nas you see.. it tooks 1.3 seconds to loads.. which is almost 68% of the whole process</p>\n\n<p>are you able to compare with joomla 2.5.3, the problem is happen in that version... <br>\nWish i have skill and capability to help you but this is more advanced than i can handle... </p>\n\n<p>Let me know what to do next... <br>\nif you wish i can do screen sharing through skype </p>', '2012-08-03 03:20:19'),
(7475004, 179, 'elkuku', '<p>I noticed in your screenshot that you are using JDump which generates a few extra warnings. Please report such tricky bugs on a plain vanilla install - just in case ;)</p>\n\n<p>Let''s peek...<br>\nCould you try and edit the following file:<br><code>libraries/joomla/string/string.php</code> on line <code>740</code> in 2.5.6 the function <code>transcode()</code><br>\nand insert a<br><code>return null;</code><br>\nright at the beginning of this function (to "disable" it) ?</p>\n\n<p>This is a piece of code i stumbled upon, that meets the "requirements" to produce this strange bug..</p>\n\n<p>BTW it''s a very strange method that converts a PHP notice into an ErrorException - I don''t believe that this is very clever..</p>\n\n<p>I think we got still a long way before we implement exceptions the way they were ment by the guys that invented them ;)</p>', '2012-08-03 03:47:37'),
(7478360, 179, 'doxadigital', '<p><a href="https://github.com/elkuku" class="user-mention">@elkuku</a> <br>\nadding in transcode function with "return null;" remove the warning, but still the problem exist...<br>\ni took testing on Exention Manager &gt; Manage.. (this page execute usort() two times : in menu and in grid)</p>\n\n<p>with return null... is faster.. you can see here: <a href="http://doxadigital.com/scrape/beforeafter.jpg">http://doxadigital.com/scrape/beforeafter.jpg</a><br>\nbut i think the bug still there</p>\n\n<p>does string.php is the one who commited this ''crime'' for over these month ?</p>', '2012-08-03 08:31:52'),
(7479773, 166, 'JoaoSRaposo', '<p>Hi,</p>\n\n<p>I''m using your version for about two months and only recently found a bug :)</p>\n\n<p>When I try to process multiple articles, for example when copying multiple articles from one category to another changing their language, I receive the following error (translated from portuguese):</p>\n\n<p>The batch process failed with the following message: Failed to archive JTableAsset :: <br> JLIB_DATABASE_QUERY_FAILED ERROR: null value in the "rules" violates the constraint not null SQL = INSERT INTO "minonl_assets" ("name", "title" , "parent_id", "level", "lft", "RGT") VALUES (''com_content.article.98'', ''Software and Human Resources Management in the Cloud'', 207,4,323,324) RETURNING id</p>\n\n<p>The result of this operation, is that only one article is copied and mantains de original language.</p>\n\n<p>In the screencast bellow you can see it happening.</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://screencast.com/t/31QjGSCiOrxL">http://screencast.com/t/31QjGSCiOrxL</a></p>\n\n<p>It''s not a serious error so I can continue working with no problem, I just want to let you now ;)</p>\n\n<p>Regards,</p>', '2012-08-03 09:50:04'),
(7502729, 166, 'gpongelli', '<p>Thank you for your reporting, I''ll try to solve this error when I''ll come back from holidays.<br>\nThat version is a little bit old, it''s in plan to update 2.5 and realize 3.0 branch with Postgresql fully supported by CMS.</p>\n\n<p>Eng. Gabriele Pongelli</p>', '2012-08-04 16:08:51'),
(7506410, 299, 'elinw', '<p>I think this should go to the template8 repo</p>', '2012-08-04 23:43:46'),
(7506433, 299, 'andreatarr', '<p>yes, sorry, we did add it there. I forgot to switch the repo again when I did the pull request</p>', '2012-08-04 23:49:08'),
(7507237, 301, 'elinw', '<p><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1431" class="issue-link" title="Handling in HttpTransport when the requested uri does not exist">joomla/joomla-platform#1431</a>  deals with some notices that show if you have error reporting on and put in a bad url.</p>\n\n<p>Feature tracker:<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28905">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28905</a></p>', '2012-08-05 02:42:14'),
(7512683, 302, 'realityking', '<p>Wrong repository.</p>', '2012-08-05 20:07:09'),
(7512744, 302, 'elinw', '<p>oops</p>', '2012-08-05 20:17:13'),
(7543650, 206, 'mahagr', '<p>What is the status of this pull request? I really think that Joomla! 3.0 should start moving towards the new platform interfaces, even if it was just an option for the 3rd party components.</p>', '2012-08-07 04:37:48'),
(7545817, 301, 'infograf768', '<p>Can''t apply patch with eclipse on master for 2 files:<br>\ncomponents/com_newsfeeds/views/newsfeed/view.html.php<br>\nand<br>\nmodules/mod_feed/tmpl/default.php</p>', '2012-08-07 07:31:51'),
(7593298, 304, 'Radek-Suski', '<p>I modified also to allow including an escaped double quotes inside the value (right-hand)<br>\nJean Marie asked also for escaped single quotes but as I can see it was always allowed so I think it is not necessary.<br>\nBeside the AFAIR, there is no need for escaping single quotes inside double quotes.</p>', '2012-08-08 18:48:09'),
(7596819, 304, 'realityking', '<p>This is awesome!</p>\n\n<p>Two things, you added some unneeded indentation could you please fix this? Also could you submit this at the platform (<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/</a>) it will than tickle down with the next merge.</p>\n\n<p>Thanks again, I was banging my head against the desk for this one but I just don''t speak regex.</p>', '2012-08-08 20:46:15'),
(7606125, 304, 'infograf768', '<p>Thanks. Works fine.</p>', '2012-08-09 06:11:19'),
(7610502, 304, 'Radek-Suski', '<p><a href="https://github.com/realityking" class="user-mention">@realityking</a> Wow, thanks a lot. After my last system wipeout I apparently forget to switch indentation to tabs in PhpStorm. <br>\nSubmitting also to platform.</p>', '2012-08-09 10:22:59'),
(7639074, 303, 'elinw', '<p>Peter please send this as a pull request to me.</p>', '2012-08-10 10:41:46'),
