(7676741, 306, 'elinw', '<p>Replaces #301</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1431" class="issue-link" title="Handling in HttpTransport when the requested uri does not exist">joomla/joomla-platform#1431</a> deals with some notices that show if you have error reporting on and put in a bad url.</p>\n\n<p>Feature tracker:<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28905">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28905</a></p>', '2012-08-12 15:30:51'),
(7677131, 306, 'realityking', '<p>JFeed will need some love to get this ready, just from a casual look I saw it''s using JXMLElement everywhere which is deprecated. The alternative is SimpleXMLElement. Also we have to change the docblocks to make this a CMS library.</p>', '2012-08-12 16:13:08'),
(7679115, 306, 'elinw', '<p>JFeed is actually working fine, I''ve done a lot of testing and it does the<br>\nsimple tasks required of it in com_newsfeed and mod_feed  as well as<br>\nsimplepie.  You''re right about the docblocks though, forget to do them this<br>\nround. Will send an update in a few hours.</p>\n\n<p>On Sun, Aug 12, 2012 at 12:13 PM, Rouven WeÃŸling<br><a href="mailto:notifications@github.com">notifications@github.com</a>wrote:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>JFeed will need some love to get this ready, just from a casual look I saw<br>\nit''s using JXMLElement everywhere which is deprecated. The alternative is<br>\nSimpleXMLElement. Also we have to change the docblocks to make this a CMS<br>\nlibrary.</p>\n\n<p>â€”<br>\nReply to this email directly or view it on GitHub<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/306#issuecomment-7677131" class="issue-link" title="Update com_newsfeeds and mod_feed to use jfeed">joomla/joomla-cms#306</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-08-12 19:41:11'),
(7679375, 306, 'mbabker', '<p>It''s not that the code doesn''t work, we''re just trying to not introduce any deprecated code usage into the CMS.  Switching from JXMLElement to SimpleXMLElement is as simple as a find/replace action.</p>', '2012-08-12 20:15:50'),
(7682924, 306, 'elinw', '<p><a href="https://github.com/realityking" class="user-mention">@realityking</a> It would be very helpful to have the needed fix to JHttpTransportSocket that has been sitting in the platform tracker for a while merged. </p>\n\n<p>Ok updated and should be working</p>', '2012-08-13 03:36:56'),
(7711445, 306, 'elinw', '<p>oops I thought  I pushed that 12 hours ago</p>', '2012-08-13 23:13:24'),
(7761299, 307, 'realityking', '<p>Ah good this resurfaces :)</p>\n\n<p>3 points:<br>\n1. This doesn''t merge right now<br>\n2. I don''t think we need all these SQL for changes to the databases since no one will update form a Joomla 2.5 postgres installation.<br>\n3. Please submit the changes to files in libraries/joomla to the platform so they can be merged over there first.</p>', '2012-08-15 16:41:52'),
(7761527, 307, 'gpongelli', '<p>Hi Rouven,<br>\n1. Why isn''t it mergeable ?<br>\n2. You''re right, these files coming from old pull request and I''ve leaved them because I''ve found same files under mysql folder.<br>\n3. There''s an open pull request for platform project about these changes at least two months old.</p>\n\n<p>Gabriele Pongelli</p>', '2012-08-15 16:50:28'),
(7761732, 307, 'realityking', '<p>Hey Gabriele,</p>\n\n<p>I don''t know what the problem is, github just tells me it can''t automatically be merged. Ideally you just update it to current master, since there hasn''t been many commits the past two days it shouldn''t be a big problem.</p>\n\n<p>You probably mean this platform pull <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/307" class="issue-link" title="PostgreSQL driver for Joomla! CMS 3.0">joomla/joomla-cms#307</a>, don''t you?</p>\n\n<p>This doesn''t contain the changes to JSessionStorageDatabase and JTable. Could you submit them separately?</p>', '2012-08-15 16:57:39'),
(7762375, 307, 'mbabker', '<p>The commit to make FinderIndexer abstract is the likely cause of the merge issue.</p>\n\n<p>Gabrielle, I abstracted out FinderIndexer so that child classes could be built for each database driver to run the indexer in a way that is optimized for that environment.  So, could you add a FinderIndexerDriverPostgresql class (you should be able to use the MySQL class as a base) and then you can modify the queries in that class to make them work best in Postgres (I have a patch doing the same for SQL Server).</p>', '2012-08-15 17:18:54'),
(7784023, 308, 'andreatarr', '<p>Tracker is <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28925">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28925</a></p>', '2012-08-16 12:35:34'),
(7786570, 308, 'infograf768', '<p>Thanks. Fixed with eclipse.</p>', '2012-08-16 14:14:21'),
(7786605, 309, 'infograf768', '<p>thanks, Fixed with eclipse</p>', '2012-08-16 14:15:20'),
(7787150, 307, 'gpongelli', '<p><a href="https://github.com/realityking" class="user-mention">@realityking</a> <br>\npull request is <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/issues/1261" class="issue-link" title="Added some method inside JDatabaseDriver to create database and alter character set">joomla/joomla-platform#1261</a> .<br>\nCan you write me git steps to do ?</p>\n\n<p>About JSessionStorageDatabase the changes I have is about str_replace as this in read()</p>\n\n<pre>str_replace(''\\0\\0\\0'', chr(0).''*''.chr(0), $result);</pre>\n\n<p>can''t you see them?<br>\nWhich is JTable change you''re referring to?</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/mbabker" class="user-mention">@mbabker</a> <br>\nI''m studying that code, I''ll add Postgresql''s version soon.</p>', '2012-08-16 14:34:36'),
(7787909, 307, 'realityking', '<p>To rebase pull request I''d follow the github instructions, they are better explained than I could ever do. The section about "Pull in upstream changes" is what you need <a href="https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo">https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo</a></p>\n\n<p>I can see the JSessionStorageDatabase fine here but we need it in the platform as well.</p>\n\n<p>Regarding JTable I mean this change: <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/307/files#diff-48">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/307/files#diff-48</a></p>\n\n<p>Also please drop the extra sql files.</p>', '2012-08-16 14:57:47'),
(7788739, 307, 'gpongelli', '<p>That is not a rebase but a merge, I hope that these steps won''t break anything, I''ll do them soon.</p>\n\n<p>About JSessionStorageDatabase and JTable I''ve added new branch for platform project, but I''ve problems with github site so I can''t actually open a new pull request.</p>\n\n<p>Which sql files do you mean? all except 3.0.0.sql ?</p>', '2012-08-16 15:24:57'),
(7789190, 307, 'realityking', '<p>All except joomla.sql and the sample data.</p>', '2012-08-16 15:38:30'),
(7801141, 128, 'elinw', '<p>Is the module not working for you? I haven''t noticed this as a problem. </p>', '2012-08-16 22:06:05'),
(7817095, 307, 'gpongelli', '<p><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/pull/1460">Here it is pull request</a> for platform about JSessionStorageDatabase and JTable.</p>', '2012-08-17 12:57:43'),
(7818480, 307, 'gpongelli', '<p>I''m merging from master branch, but I''ve too many conflicts on </p><pre>installation/models/database.php</pre> about a commit of one day ago .\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/realityking" class="user-mention">@realityking</a> <br>\nIMHO you should have look at my code before merge <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/commit/9b3bd996c9609b4b54663c34bbf3936cb393a8e9">this commit</a> that breaks installation on PostgreSQL .</p>', '2012-08-17 13:57:04'),
(7828402, 311, 'infograf768', '<p>Thank you and no thank you for now ;)<br>\nWe will ask all Translation teams to update their ini files when we will freeze the installation before stable.</p>', '2012-08-17 16:51:49'),
(7840773, 312, 'realityking', '<p>Unfortunately it''s not that easy. Developers sometimes do use different MIME types so we can''t just render no type attribute when in HTML mode.</p>', '2012-08-18 01:44:19'),
(7841535, 69, 'elinw', '<p>This is so old</p>', '2012-08-18 04:00:21'),
(7843341, 285, 'infograf768', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28849">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28849</a></p>', '2012-08-18 10:05:02'),
(7844862, 312, 'phproberto', '<p>Are you talking about custom mime types not in this list?<br><a href="http://www.webmaster-toolkit.com/mime-types.shtml">http://www.webmaster-toolkit.com/mime-types.shtml</a></p>', '2012-08-18 14:24:19'),
(7845068, 312, 'realityking', '<p>Just as an example take this snippet: <a href="http://ejohn.org/blog/javascript-micro-templating/">http://ejohn.org/blog/javascript-micro-templating/</a></p>\n\n<p>In more general terms, HTML5 still allows different MIME types for script elements (and link too but that''s a bit different). HTML5''s change is only that there''s now a default value if the attribute is not present.</p>', '2012-08-18 14:48:56'),
(7845482, 313, 'infograf768', '<p>Committed through eclipse</p>', '2012-08-18 15:38:26'),
(7846383, 314, 'infograf768', '<p>We are aware of the issue. Can you create a tracker on joomlacode?</p>', '2012-08-18 17:33:53'),
(7847719, 312, 'nternetinspired', '<p>html is simply more forgiving now. As i understand it (the official spec isn''t an easy read) it is also not really the case that there is a default value for these assets (not just js), instead the browser checks what type the file is and proceeds on that basis. The browser checks whatever the case.</p>\n\n<p>Thus declaring an incorrect type attribute should not work because the browser will determine the file type and ignore the type attribute. At that point, type attributes are superfluous at best. Current recommendations are that type attributes are not used and, as we will be touting a shiny ''we''re all html5'' badge, I think we should do the best we can to match best practice.</p>', '2012-08-18 20:23:53'),
(7848196, 312, 'realityking', '<p>No, no, no.</p>\n\n<p>Well not quite. Browsers do take the type attribute into account. Sane browsers (which means all but IE, IE can be forced to this behavior with a HTTP header) don''t sniff for content.</p>\n\n<p>The HTML5 spec says for the type element on the link element:</p>\n\n<pre><code>For external resource links, the type attribute is used as a hint to user agents so that they can avoid fetching resources they do not support. If the attribute is present, then the user agent must assume that the resource is of the given type (even if that is not a valid MIME type, e.g. the empty string). If the attribute is omitted, but the external resource link type has a default type defined, then the user agent must assume that the resource is of that type. If the UA does not support the given MIME type for the given link relationship, then the UA should not obtain the resource; if the UA does support the given MIME type for the given link relationship, then the UA should obtain the resource at the appropriate time as specified for the external resource link''s particular type. If the attribute is omitted, and the external resource link type does not have a default type defined, but the user agent would obtain the resource if the type was known and supported, then the user agent should obtain the resource under the assumption that it will be supported.\n\nUser agents must not consider the type attribute authoritative â€” upon fetching the resource, user agents must not use the type attribute to determine its actual type. Only the actual type (as defined in the next paragraph) is used to determine whether to apply the resource, not the aforementioned assumed type.\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>By obtaining the actual type is not content sniffing meant but relying on the <code>Content-Type</code> header.</p>\n\n<p>For the script element (which is more relevant because it gets trickier):</p>\n\n<pre><code>The type attribute gives the language of the script or format of the data. If the attribute is present, its value must be a valid MIME type. The charset parameter must not be specified. The default, which is used if the attribute is absent, is "text/javascript".\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And for information why content sniffing is not a good thing I recommend: <a href="http://www.h-online.com/security/features/Risky-MIME-sniffing-in-Internet-Explorer-746229.html">http://www.h-online.com/security/features/Risky-MIME-sniffing-in-Internet-Explorer-746229.html</a></p>', '2012-08-18 21:18:35'),
(7848630, 312, 'realityking', '<p>BTW I just noticed against what repro this was done. This would have to be fixed in the platform, not the CMS.</p>', '2012-08-18 22:17:38'),
(7849262, 312, 'phproberto', '<p><a href="https://github.com/realityking" class="user-mention">@realityking</a>  Oops! you are true. I''ll have no problem in submitting it to platform before merging this but can we finish the debate here? </p>\n\n<p>What about something like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>    // Generate stylesheet links\n    foreach ($document-&gt;_styleSheets as $strSrc =&gt; $strAttr)\n    {\n        $buffer .= $tab . ''&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="'' . $strSrc . ''"'';\n        if (!is_null($strAttr[''mime'']) &amp;&amp; (!$document-&gt;isHtml5() || ($document-&gt;isHtml5() &amp;&amp; $strAttr[''mime''] != ''text/css'')))\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' type="'' . $strAttr[''mime''] . ''"'';\n        }\n        if (!is_null($strAttr[''media'']))\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' media="'' . $strAttr[''media''] . ''"'';\n        }\n        if ($temp = JArrayHelper::toString($strAttr[''attribs'']))\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' '' . $temp;\n        }\n        $buffer .= $tagEnd . $lnEnd;\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This way we will remove the type if it''s the standard type but keep it when it''s a custom one. For javascript maybe an in_array with all the javascript types commonly used (text/javascript is the default type in HTML5 but is marked as obsolete by IANA that recommends application/javascript ....that doesn''t work on IE9..... ). So for example something like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>    // Generate script file links\n    foreach ($document-&gt;_scripts as $strSrc =&gt; $strAttr)\n    {\n        $buffer .= $tab . ''&lt;script src="'' . $strSrc . ''"'';\n        $defaultMimes = array(\n            ''text/javascript'', ''application/javascript'', ''text/x-javascript'', ''application/x-javascript''\n        );\n        if (!is_null($strAttr[''mime'']) &amp;&amp; (!$document-&gt;isHtml5() || ($document-&gt;isHtml5() &amp;&amp; !in_array($strAttr[''mime''], $defaultMimes)) ))\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' type="'' . $strAttr[''mime''] . ''"'';\n        }\n        if ($strAttr[''defer''])\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' defer="defer"'';\n        }\n        if ($strAttr[''async''])\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' async="async"'';\n        }\n        $buffer .= ''&gt;&lt;/script&gt;'' . $lnEnd;\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will allow developers to remove types keeping the flexibility for use custom mime types.</p>', '2012-08-18 23:56:17'),
(7850015, 312, 'realityking', '<p>Yeah we can finish the debate here. Just please link to this page for any final pull request made to the platform.</p>\n\n<p>That would work. It could actually be a bit simplified:</p>\n\n<pre><code>// Generate script file links\n    foreach ($document-&gt;_scripts as $strSrc =&gt; $strAttr)\n    {\n        $buffer .= $tab . ''&lt;script src="'' . $strSrc . ''"'';\n        $defaultMimes = array(\n            ''text/javascript'', ''application/javascript'', ''text/x-javascript'', ''application/x-javascript''\n        );\n        if (!is_null($strAttr[''mime'']) &amp;&amp; (!$document-&gt;isHtml5() || !in_array($strAttr[''mime''], $defaultMimes)))\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' type="'' . $strAttr[''mime''] . ''"'';\n        }\n        if ($strAttr[''defer''])\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' defer="defer"'';\n        }\n        if ($strAttr[''async''])\n        {\n            $buffer .= '' async="async"'';\n        }\n        $buffer .= ''&gt;&lt;/script&gt;'' . $lnEnd;\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I have to read up on the different javascript MIME types but IIRC correctly they only have a subtle different when sent as the <code>Content-Type</code> header but not in the HTML type attribute.</p>\n\n<p>Question now is if it''s worth it ;) (I don''t care either way, I just wanna keep the ability to set other MIME types)</p>', '2012-08-19 02:26:10'),
(7856866, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>Screenshot of result: <a href="http://quick-markup.com/p/503155c8481a5">http://quick-markup.com/p/503155c8481a5</a></p>', '2012-08-19 21:08:43'),
(7857623, 316, 'mbabker', '<p>Could you update the Less file(s) too?</p>', '2012-08-19 22:36:55'),
(7864732, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>I removed the btn-micro stuff.<br>\nChanging the code to make it use btn-mini also affects other buttons (like the lock) which you do want as btn-micro. So will have to look into it deeper or just leave it.</p>', '2012-08-20 09:38:48'),
(7870258, 312, 'phproberto', '<p>Thanks!</p>\n\n<p>I''ve commited as suggested. If you give me the Ok I''ll make a pull request to the platform.</p>', '2012-08-20 14:11:49'),
(7877417, 316, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker on joomlacode.<br>\nThere is already one related. <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28944">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28944</a></p>', '2012-08-20 17:52:43'),
(7884359, 316, 'kyleledbetter', '<p>The latest update using less and going w/ the btn success/warning/danger/etc colors looks much better</p>', '2012-08-20 21:36:38'),
(7888910, 314, 'bcordis', '<p>Ok I''ll do that tonight.</p>\n\n<p>Sent from my iPhone</p>\n\n<p>On Aug 18, 2012, at 12:33 PM, infograf768 <a href="mailto:notifications@github.com">notifications@github.com</a> wrote:</p>\n\n<p>We are aware of the issue. Can you create a tracker on joomlacode?</p>\n\n<p>â€”<br>\nReply to this email directly or view it on<br>\nGitHub<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/314#issuecomment-7846383" class="issue-link" title="Component options button routing error">joomla/joomla-cms#314</a>.</p>', '2012-08-21 01:14:57'),
(7893813, 316, 'infograf768', '<p>I suggest using a different icon for Default and Featured, or at least a different color.<br>\nMaybe the capital A ?<br><a href="http://postimage.org/image/41pxuvua7/">http://postimage.org/image/41pxuvua7/</a></p>', '2012-08-21 07:34:55'),
(7893997, 316, 'simbus82', '<p>Ohhh this is very nice! Colors are really important for usability!</p>', '2012-08-21 07:45:28'),
(7896078, 317, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker item on joomlacode</p>', '2012-08-21 09:33:19'),
(7896526, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>Tracker <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28962">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28962</a></p>', '2012-08-21 09:55:09'),
(7896604, 317, 'nonumber', '<p>Tracker: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28963">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28963</a></p>', '2012-08-21 09:58:57'),
(7909018, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>Because it is redundant. CSS for .icon-trash:before is defined a few lines further:</p>\n\n<pre><code>.icon-purge:before,\n.icon-trash:before {\n  content: "\\4c";\n}\n</code></pre>', '2012-08-21 17:31:42'),
(7909055, 316, 'realityking', '<p>Gotcha.</p>', '2012-08-21 17:32:55'),
(7909453, 316, 'kyleledbetter', '<p>I agree, it would be nice to leave the star for featured and use something different for default. Here''s the list <a href="http://kyleledbetter.com/icomoon/">http://kyleledbetter.com/icomoon/</a><br>\nI''m thinking icon-bookmark or icon-pin (i''m aware that those could also have different connotations)</p>', '2012-08-21 17:45:06'),
(7909619, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>What about icon-flag?</p>', '2012-08-21 17:49:09'),
(7909685, 316, 'realityking', '<p>How about the flag for featured and the star for default? That''d be my intuition. </p>', '2012-08-21 17:50:37'),
(7909694, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>We could also keep the star for default too, just via another classname, so that the color can be different (blue).</p>', '2012-08-21 17:50:48'),
(7909773, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>I think icon-bookmark would be ok for default too... but not sure it looks like anything when used inside a button.</p>', '2012-08-21 17:52:21'),
(7917120, 307, 'gpongelli', '<p>Is this branch mergeable now ?</p>\n\n<p>I''ve removed all sql files and added FinderIndexerDriverPostgresql class, not tested but commented Mysql specific queries.<br>\nDo not merge this branch now, I''m working on installation/models/database.php file yet.</p>', '2012-08-21 21:32:42'),
(7917340, 307, 'realityking', '<p>Yes it is :)</p>', '2012-08-21 21:39:51'),
(7918805, 307, 'mbabker', '<p>I have PostgreSQL set up, so I can test the Finder work here.  I am trying to get my SQL Server class committed too, which I believe touches some of the same queries in common areas, so we are on the right track there.</p>', '2012-08-21 22:30:26'),
(7926759, 316, 'infograf768', '<p>icon-bookmark looks good for featured<br><a href="http://s19.postimage.org/n5sy9mfbn/Screen_Shot_2012_08_22_at_09_16_48.png">http://s19.postimage.org/n5sy9mfbn/Screen_Shot_2012_08_22_at_09_16_48.png</a></p>\n\n<p>pin may be too thin, here in gold, but IMHO, it is the icon which best describe the function</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://s19.postimage.org/rsz0be2oj/pin.png">http://s19.postimage.org/rsz0be2oj/pin.png</a></p>\n\n<p>maybe flag is also too thin<br><a href="http://s19.postimage.org/edbzlxu6r/flag.png">http://s19.postimage.org/edbzlxu6r/flag.png</a></p>\n\n<p>Suggestion: normalize Pinned Banners to use the same icon as Featured.</p>\n\n<p>We should keep the star for Default, as this has always been used for that purpose.</p>', '2012-08-22 07:36:30'),
(7927554, 317, 'nonumber', '<p>synced with master (again!)</p>', '2012-08-22 08:20:49'),
(7927680, 316, 'simbus82', '<p>Joomla! for "featured/home page/default" uses a star from ages, i think we should keep using it...</p>', '2012-08-22 08:26:55'),
(7931708, 316, 'pjwiseman', '<p>I think they would all be ok especially given the presence of the descriptive button above.</p>\n\n<p>The "pinned" might be better used for articles pinned to the top of a blog.  I like the clean look of the bookmark, but I think the flag is a better context.</p>\n\n<p>Is there any major reason to avoid the star?  We have the Home Menu, Default Templates and Featured Articles which are all different contexts so can''t readily be confused.</p>', '2012-08-22 11:49:49'),
(7937696, 316, 'infograf768', '<p>Featured does not use the star in 2.5.<br>\nHome was using it indeed, but the new icon is great for it.</p>', '2012-08-22 15:18:21'),
(7937798, 316, 'simbus82', '<p>In 2.5 is a circle with a star inside...</p>', '2012-08-22 15:21:20'),
(7944728, 316, 'kyleledbetter', '<p>I think it makes sense to keep the (gold colored) icon-star for default. For featured, icon-pin seems to make the most sense to me. Maybe we keep the gold color for the star and we can use purple or some other color for the featured pin. Thanks for thinking through this everyone, good discussion</p>', '2012-08-22 18:44:10'),
(7952056, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>Like this?<br><a href="http://quick-markup.com/p/50354a77484a7">http://quick-markup.com/p/50354a77484a7</a></p>', '2012-08-22 21:09:28'),
(7952134, 316, 'nonumber', '<p>Or does this look better: using icon-bookmark<br><a href="http://quick-markup.com/p/50354b24ed60d">http://quick-markup.com/p/50354b24ed60d</a></p>', '2012-08-22 21:12:31'),
(7954814, 316, 'realityking', '<p>How about blue for featured? IIRC that was the color used in 2.5, it might help people gasping that intuitively.</p>', '2012-08-22 22:51:48'),
(7956439, 323, 'elinw', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28975">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28975</a></p>', '2012-08-23 00:16:29'),
(7962876, 320, 'infograf768', '<p>Thank you, but we will update the installation ini files when we freeze the strings (that will be between beta and stable) and are sure we have a Translation Team for Lithuanian for 3.0.<br>\nAt this time, the installation ini files are just the 2.5.6 ones. </p>', '2012-08-23 08:17:06'),
(7964318, 320, 'vipantonio', '<p>But I''ve seen many pull requests (closed) similar to my. I''ve been a member of translation team since Joomla 1.5, maybe somehow I should be approved officialy, or this is not an issue?</p>', '2012-08-23 09:25:57'),
(7970308, 321, 'realityking', '<p>I''d wait for this dependending on the outcome of #312</p>\n\n<p>Also if we merge this it should use double quotes, not single quotes.</p>', '2012-08-23 13:57:15'),
(7971869, 320, 'infograf768', '<p>We have not committed any changes to the installation ini files, except for en-AU and en-US, which are basically the same as en-GB.<br>\nThe other languages will be done when language freeze is declared and call to Translation Teams will be made to get those who commit to produce a 3.0 pack to update their installation ini. Other inis will be deleted from 3.0 (Translation Policy)<br>\nFYI, Lithuanian language situation in general is now discussed. You may contact me personally by mail about that.</p>', '2012-08-23 14:44:17'),
(7984220, 319, 'elinw', '<p>Superceded by another pull request</p>', '2012-08-23 21:11:19'),
(7984396, 297, 'elinw', '<p>I''m sorry Peter would you mind updating to current trunk on this? Some of the patched files have been taken out.</p>', '2012-08-23 21:17:11'),
(7984414, 166, 'gpongelli', '<p>Hi Joao,<br>\nactually I''m working on porting this driver to 3.0 , could you test if this<br>\nerror is present with this zip ?<br><a href="https://github.com/gpongelli/joomla-cms/zipball/postgresql_3.0">https://github.com/gpongelli/joomla-cms/zipball/postgresql_3.0</a></p>\n\n<p>Actually I haven''t a 2.5 installation so I can''t replicate nor debug this<br>\nerror.</p>\n\n<p>Thank you,<br>\nEng. Gabriele Pongelli.</p>\n\n<p>2012/8/4 Gabriele Pongelli <a href="mailto:gabriele.pongelli@gmail.com">gabriele.pongelli@gmail.com</a></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thank you for your reporting, I''ll try to solve this error when I''ll come<br>\nback from holidays.<br>\nThat version is a little bit old, it''s in plan to update 2.5 and realize<br>\n3.0 branch with Postgresql fully supported by CMS.</p>\n\n<p>Eng. Gabriele Pongelli</p>\n\n<p>AVVERTENZE AI SENSI DEL D.LGS. 196/2003<br>\nLe informazioni contenute in questo messaggio di posta elettronica e negli<br>\neventuali files allegati, sono da considerarsi strettamente riservati. Il<br>\nloro utilizzo Ã¨ consentito esclusivamente al destinatario del messaggio,<br>\nper le finalitÃ  indicate nel messaggio stesso. Qualora riceveste per errore<br>\nquesto messaggio, Vi preghiamo cortesemente di darcene notizia<br>\nall''indirizzo e-mail di cui sopra e di procedere alla distruzione del<br>\nmessaggio stesso, cancellandolo dal Vostro sistema; costituisce<br>\ncomportamento contrario ai principi dettati dal D.lgs. 196/2003 il<br>\ntrattenere il messaggio stesso, divulgarlo anche in parte, distribuirlo ad<br>\naltri soggetti, copiarlo, od utilizzarlo per finalitÃ  diverse.<br>\nThis electronic transmission is strictly confidential and intended solely<br>\nfor the addresses. It may contain information which is covered by legal,<br>\nprofessional or other privilege. If you are not the intended addressee, you<br>\nmust not disclose, copy or take any action in reliance of this<br>\ntransmission. If you have received this transmission in error, please<br>\nnotify us and delete the received data as soon as possible.</p>\n\n<p>Il giorno 03/ago/2012, alle ore 12:50, JoaoSRaposo&lt;<br><a href="mailto:reply@reply.github.com">reply@reply.github.com</a>&gt;<br>\nha scritto:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi,</p>\n\n<p>I''m using your version for about two months and only recently found a<br>\nbug :)</p>\n\n<p>When I try to process multiple articles, for example when copying<br>\nmultiple articles from one category to another changing their language, I<br>\nreceive the following error (translated from portuguese):</p>\n\n<p>The batch process failed with the following message: Failed to archive<br>\nJTableAsset :: <br> JLIB_DATABASE_QUERY_FAILED ERROR: null value in the<br>\n"rules" violates the constraint not null SQL = INSERT INTO "minonl_assets"<br>\n("name", "title" , "parent_id", "level", "lft", "RGT") VALUES<br>\n(''com_content.article.98'', ''Software and Human Resources Management in the<br>\nCloud'', 207,4,323,324) RETURNING id</p>\n\n<p>The result of this operation, is that only one article is copied and<br>\nmantains de original language.</p>\n\n<p>In the screencast bellow you can see it happening.</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://screencast.com/t/31QjGSCiOrxL">http://screencast.com/t/31QjGSCiOrxL</a></p>\n\n<p>It''s not a serious error so I can continue working with no problem, I<br>\njust want to let you now ;)</p>\n\n<p>Regards,</p>\n\n<hr>\n<p>Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/166#issuecomment-7479773" class="issue-link" title="PostgreSQL driver for Joomla! CMS. [v2] - [DEPRECATED]">joomla/joomla-cms#166</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>', '2012-08-23 21:17:46'),
(7986314, 226, 'elinw', '<p>still valid i think</p>', '2012-08-23 22:24:58'),
(7986637, 327, 'realityking', '<p>Like we did with JFolder we should probably review what other files are missing the jimport for JFile. Would you be intrested in doing that? (You just need to grep for JFile and for the corespnding jimport. Those files in the first but not the second list need to be patched) </p>', '2012-08-23 22:36:44'),
(7987066, 297, 'pjwiseman', '<p>It will take a bit of time.  Conflicts with sql files (joomla.sql and three sample files) but they don''t look too hard to resolve.</p>', '2012-08-23 22:55:27'),
(7989546, 327, 'elinw', '<p>Were was this removal documented? Have other applications beside the cms been given  timely notice (i.e. minimum one full 3 month tagged release of the platform with deprecation notice in place)? </p>', '2012-08-24 01:12:13'),
(7990926, 327, 'mbabker', '<p>This was more dependency management cleanup than removing API if I understand right.  Basically, classes were loading other classes that they didn''t need to, or were modified to not depend on, and other classes depended on those imported classes to already be there instead of handling their dependencies on their own.</p>', '2012-08-24 03:01:04'),
(7996221, 327, 'realityking', '<p>Any file/class is responsible for loading all non-autoloadable classes. Just relying on it being loaded by something else is doomed to fail when that something else changes.</p>\n\n<p>Nothing in JFile has been removed, a couple of methods have been deprecated though and so it''s used less often now.</p>', '2012-08-24 09:09:29'),
(8000049, 327, 'juliopontes', '<p>This not affect 1.5.X because dont have copy functionality.</p>', '2012-08-24 12:36:36'),
(8007244, 329, 'realityking', '<p>What Joomla version did you use to test?</p>', '2012-08-24 16:19:27'),
(8008479, 321, 'case303', '<p>cool, as long as someone is aware..  I''ll close the pull request then.</p>', '2012-08-24 17:04:14'),
(8012254, 327, 'elinw', '<p>So let''s get this one merged and make it a huge priority to find places where there is breakage because dependencies were removed without adequate testing/accounting for downstream for breakage.  This is why Michael is right  about unit tests but nothing with potential dependency in other classes should  be removed without fixing all of those at the same time. We can''t have a broken trunk.<br>\nCan one of you generate a list of all classes where this import was removed and then we can grep for classes where those are called.<br>\nBut let''s not hold up this merge for the sake of that.</p>', '2012-08-24 19:24:38'),
(8019994, 330, 'elinw', '<p>There''s already a pull request for this and issue in the cms tracker!</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28984">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=28984</a></p>\n\n<p>Would you mind testing that so we can get it in asap?</p>', '2012-08-25 04:18:40'),
