(8299558, 317, 'pjwiseman', '<p>I''m struggling with commit 127c374, the "merge remote tracking branch remotes/upstream/master".  I''m hoping someone better versed in joomla''s use of git can give that the ok or not ok.  When I merge to my own fresh master I get a merge tree that doesn''t clearly distinguish the changes in this pull.  The merge is valid - it''s simply how it is presented.  When refreshing to the current master, I generally do a rebase, create a new pull request, and close the old one, which is a pain.  I don''t know whether there is a cleaner way - we''re all new to git.</p>\n\n<p>UPDATE: The word is that the upstream merge is ok.  This history isn''t necessarily as clean, but it works.</p>', '2012-09-05 13:56:27'),
(8299638, 317, 'nonumber', '<p>Thanks Peter,</p>\n\n<p>Changed the grid method to take the tooltip title as extra value:<br><a href="https://github.com/nonumber/joomla-cms/commit/ca0cc442671ef2b719930314fc5db6cb62b562cb" class="commit-link">nonumber/joomla-cms@<tt>ca0cc44</tt></a></p>\n\n<p>Rouven is aware of the differences between platform files (bootstrap stuff) and he is on it...<br>\nThere are more than just these changes that still have to get ported to platform.</p>', '2012-09-05 13:59:22'),
