(9197397, 478, 'infograf768', '<p>Thanks.</p>', '2012-10-06 11:31:40'),
(9197569, 478, 'Chraneco', '<p>Sorry, I have forgotten to link back to the tracker item:<br><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29446">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29446</a><br>\nIt can be marked as ''Fixed'' now.</p>', '2012-10-06 12:01:22'),
(9214240, 332, 'pjwiseman', '<p>Closing.  For reference, the 2.5 fix is at <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/334" class="issue-link" title="Usernotes4 25x">joomla/joomla-cms#334</a></p>', '2012-10-08 00:37:41'),
(9217899, 482, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed with Eclipse.</p>', '2012-10-08 07:13:08'),
(9244836, 472, 'phproberto', '<p>Tracker issue:</p>\n\n<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29428">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29428</a></p>', '2012-10-09 00:04:53'),
(9267345, 465, 'mahagr', '<p>I''m really not sure why there needs to be a hit counter for the category. I cannot find a reason why I would like to know how many times one particular category has been visited.</p>', '2012-10-09 16:01:44'),
(9267581, 479, 'mahagr', '<p>There are a few like this, but they all come from deprecated code. I would ignore fixing this "issue" as it helps extension developers to get rid of the old code.</p>', '2012-10-09 16:08:02'),
(9267867, 472, 'mahagr', '<p>With this fix: what happens if you rename the article alias from the backend?</p>\n\n<p>Q: Should the old links keep up working?</p>', '2012-10-09 16:14:22'),
(9269881, 472, 'juliopontes', '<p><a href="https://github.com/mahagr" class="user-mention">@mahagr</a> No, they get recent alias field in db. So if you change You should get a error/404 page.</p>', '2012-10-09 17:09:52'),
(9270591, 472, 'mahagr', '<p>In my humble opinion breaking all the links from Google isn''t that good idea administrator decides to change the alias -- at least not if the behaviour was different before and there''s a way to find out article ID.</p>\n\n<p>There''s also another major drawback on this fix -- I''ve seen many URLs from coming from both older versions of Joomla and other extensions that do not add alias to the article name. So your change is likely to break a few links which were working before.</p>\n\n<p>Better way to deal with the issue would force redirect if the URL of the article isn''t correct (e.g. was renamed or the generated link was missing alias).</p>', '2012-10-09 17:30:06'),
(9273213, 472, 'phproberto', '<p><a href="https://github.com/mahagr" class="user-mention">@mahagr</a> I think that you misunderstood what this patch does. It doesn''t break anything, just fixes the expected behaviour of the content URLs.</p>\n\n<p>If you change the alias of an article is because you want to change the URL. You can keep the old alias or if you want to change the alias and keep the old URL working you should create a redirection from the old url to the new URL. </p>\n\n<p>Extensions should use JRoute to generate valid URLs. Don''t fix a bug because some extensions are badly programmed has no sense to me.</p>', '2012-10-09 18:24:55'),
(9273743, 472, 'phproberto', '<p>We are almost there JÃºlio.</p>\n\n<p>I have added two files Joomla! standards validation as example of remaining issues. Available if needed to help you to setup CodeSniffer working.</p>', '2012-10-09 18:39:21'),
(9275854, 465, 'phproberto', '<p>I probably will not use it also but it isn''t so strange that someone does it. If the field is there why not use it?</p>\n\n<p>But I''m going to ensure that the hit counter is shown inthe backend as it does in the article management!</p>', '2012-10-09 19:33:33'),
(9285464, 472, 'juliopontes', '<p><a href="https://github.com/phproberto" class="user-mention">@phproberto</a>  please check. </p>', '2012-10-10 00:43:02'),
(9287736, 490, 'mbabker', '<p>Hathor''s submenu has never been designed to be loaded within the component area, which was the reason we had to keep mod_submenu working.  Yes, the submenu is restored, but if it is going to be below the toolbar as you''ve placed it, within the component area, the styling needs to change.  The tab styling does not work here anymore.</p>', '2012-10-10 01:58:11'),
(9288237, 490, 'shumisha', '<p>Hi Michael. You could not "keep the module working". It suffered the same issue that caused its removal from the main cms branch. I actually never saw Hathor design with sub menu, so I first simply restoredbthe full functinality, and it looked ''ok'' to me. Can you elaborate on what''s not working with tabs?</p>', '2012-10-10 02:32:10'),
(9288289, 490, 'mbabker', '<p>It works, but the styling is way off.</p>\n\n<p>With this patch - <a href="http://awesomescreenshot.com/0a6inqq9d">http://awesomescreenshot.com/0a6inqq9d</a></p>\n\n<p>From 2.5 - <a href="http://awesomescreenshot.com/01ainqu27">http://awesomescreenshot.com/01ainqu27</a></p>\n\n<p>To assume the position that you''re proposing, the styling should change IMO.  It just doesn''t look right in that spot.</p>\n\n<p>Sorry if I''ve come across a little harsh at times.  Working hard, not a lot of sleep, and been easily irritable as of late.</p>', '2012-10-10 02:37:14'),
(9288374, 490, 'shumisha', '<p>I know that, close to 5am here. Styling doesn''t look way off though. Won''t be be able to work again on this again before a couple of days though</p>', '2012-10-10 02:41:47'),
(9289932, 465, 'mahagr', '<p>I''m just wondering why not to remove that field from the database instead...?</p>', '2012-10-10 04:42:09'),
(9290190, 243, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>Hmm. It seems this was never picked up before 3.0 and now parts of it are obsolete. </p>', '2012-10-10 05:06:12'),
(9290237, 472, 'mahagr', '<p>Using just JRoute doesn''t work. By default it generates URLs without slugs in it. In order to get aliases right, you need to know exactly how to do that -- including ContentHelperRoute::getArticleRoute() call with ''id:slug'' format in the parameters.</p>\n\n<p>Most people do not know how to do that as there''s no documentation on it. And the rest of us have just copied the code from Joomla. But I''ve observed some cases when alias doesn''t get added to the article name even if it should -- in other sites the same code is working.</p>', '2012-10-10 05:11:05'),
(9293906, 490, 'shumisha', '<p>Follow up: had a quick look, styling changes don''t look so simple to me, so if anyone can step in, that''s more likely to bring this fix to completion. Thanks</p>', '2012-10-10 08:36:39'),
(9301778, 472, 'phproberto', '<p><a href="https://github.com/mahagr" class="user-mention">@mahagr</a> </p>\n\n<p>ContentHelperRoute::getArticleRoute() function receives article id and category id as parameters:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static function getArticleRoute($id, $catid = 0, $language = 0)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Not so hard to understand. But even if you do something:</p>\n\n<pre><code>JRoute::_(''index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=22'');\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It still generates an ugly URL like "component/content/article?id=22" that works perfectly.</p>\n\n<p>Receiving only the article id like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>require_once JPATH_SITE.''/components/com_content/helpers/route.php'';\nJRoute::_(ContentHelperRoute::getArticleRoute(22));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Can generate the correct SEF URL that works. </p>\n\n<p>Changing that SEF URL is what this patch checks and should not be allowed if you don''t define a custom redirection.</p>\n\n<p><a href="https://github.com/juliopontes" class="user-mention">@juliopontes</a> </p>\n\n<p>Applying the current patch fails (another missing ";" ). You should check the patch before commiting.</p>\n\n<p>Also you fixed a few errors but you reintroduced standard validation errors :( This is going to be ethernal if you don''t setup codeSniffer.</p>\n\n<p>Do you want me to make a pull request into your commit to fix remaining issues?</p>', '2012-10-10 12:59:57'),
(9306418, 472, 'juliopontes', '<p><a href="https://github.com/phproberto" class="user-mention">@phproberto</a> yep, please help me.</p>', '2012-10-10 15:07:42'),
(9322623, 494, 'dextercowley', '<p>Closing. This was an example for a Git tutorial on the wiki. </p>', '2012-10-10 22:48:48'),
(9325738, 475, 'youjoomla', '<p>here is the fix </p>\n\n<p>if (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'') { <br>\n(function($) { <br>\n       $(document).ready(function(){<br>\n        $(''.carousel'').each(function(index, element) {<br>\n                $(this)[index].slide = null;<br>\n               });<br>\n         });<br>\n })(jQuery);<br>\n}</p>\n\n<p>we can also check for existence of mootools first before doing this like</p>\n\n<p>if (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'' &amp;&amp; typeof MooTools != ''undefined'' )  { <br>\n// both present , kill jquery slide for carousel class<br>\n(function($) {Â <br>\nÂ  Â  Â  Â $(document).ready(function(){<br>\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  $(''.carousel'').each(function(index, element) {<br>\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  $(this)[index].slide = null;<br>\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â });<br>\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â });<br>\nÂ })(jQuery);<br>\n}</p>\n\n<p>this fix is suggested by jq bug squad <br><a href="http://bugs.jqueryui.com/ticket/4168">http://bugs.jqueryui.com/ticket/4168</a></p>', '2012-10-11 01:25:31'),
(9329313, 448, 'Chraneco', '<p>This was merged, so I''m closing it.</p>', '2012-10-11 05:51:57'),
(9335168, 475, 'judgestone', '<p>Worked a treat, thank you youjoomla.</p>', '2012-10-11 10:23:11'),
(9407307, 498, 'HermanPeeren', '<p>Although I think this is not the appropriate place to ask user questions (that''s where fora are for), I assume you refer to J! 3.0: parent option is on the Options tab of the categories.</p>', '2012-10-13 18:29:24'),
(9408069, 498, 'jamesjwarren', '<p>Sorry, I was assuming it was a bug but just my eyes! I have found it at the bottom of the details tab. I think the issue was that when I was using the code mirror editor the page appears to be blank as there is no visual box for the description. Although the options are still there upon scrolling!</p>\n\n<p><a target="_blank" href="https://a248.e.akamai.net/camo.github.com/cc5adb7bc86f5e78abd4d41f0de96fea355c76ab/687474703a2f2f6a616d65732e676f6c64656e68617a652e636f2e756b2f696d616765732f4a335f63617465676f72795f64657461696c732e4a5047"><img src="https://a248.e.akamai.net/camo.github.com/cc5adb7bc86f5e78abd4d41f0de96fea355c76ab/687474703a2f2f6a616d65732e676f6c64656e68617a652e636f2e756b2f696d616765732f4a335f63617465676f72795f64657461696c732e4a5047" alt="J3 Category Details" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>', '2012-10-13 18:49:26'),
(9416689, 495, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed with eclipse.Thanks.</p>', '2012-10-14 06:31:23'),
(9416756, 496, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed with eclipse. Thanks</p>', '2012-10-14 06:46:25'),
(9416934, 486, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed with eclipse. Thanks.</p>', '2012-10-14 07:21:09'),
(9428482, 499, 'elinw', '<p>Yup ... Why people should not have such long line lengths :P.</p>', '2012-10-14 22:13:32'),
(9429888, 391, 'javigomez', '<p>The file have been contributed (<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/commits/master/templates/beez3/favicon.ico">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/commits/master/templates/beez3/favicon.ico</a>) so I''m closing the pull request </p>', '2012-10-15 00:36:14'),
(9439583, 499, 'infograf768', '<p>New patch proposed on joomlacode</p>', '2012-10-15 09:47:41'),
(9444053, 501, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker on joomlacode, give testing instructions (I get the notice in logs when clicking on the select position when editing a module) and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-10-15 13:05:38'),
(9447976, 475, 'jwhelan72', '<p>Where does that go to correct the conflict problem?</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>JW</li>\n</ul>', '2012-10-15 14:59:03'),
(9476675, 475, 'judgestone', '<p>Insert it into your template index.php file.</p>', '2012-10-16 08:29:05'),
(9477194, 475, 'jwhelan72', '<p>I did and it works great. Thank you!</p>\n\n<p>And, I have jQuery, Mootools, and Bootstrap all running at the same time. (stupid I know).</p>\n\n<p>Thanks again.</p>', '2012-10-16 08:48:10'),
(9477293, 464, 'svanschu', '<p><a href="http://www.diigo.com/item/image/25qjf/wkqm">http://www.diigo.com/item/image/25qjf/wkqm</a></p>', '2012-10-16 08:51:52'),
(9495981, 503, 'infograf768', '<p>The isis error has been corrected in master.on October 14th<br>\nClosing.</p>', '2012-10-16 16:04:37'),
(9496129, 464, 'infograf768', '<p>I do not doubt you get the error, but I can''t reproduce on master, or 3.0.1<br>\nWhich version of joomla are you using.<br>\nI suggest you update.</p>', '2012-10-16 16:08:35'),
(9496240, 475, 'infograf768', '<p>if the fix does not concern J! core, please close Issue.</p>', '2012-10-16 16:11:42'),
(9507812, 475, 'youjoomla', '<p>This should concern the core since jq bootsrtap and moo run together. This should be added in head or in bootstrap js to check for mootools existence .</p>', '2012-10-16 21:34:14'),
(9508021, 475, 'mbabker', '<p>We''ve already added modifications to the bootstrap.js files for one of the other conflicts, so I personally don''t see a huge issue with modifying that file directly so long as the change is clearly indicated in the file.  Check <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/master/media/jui/js/bootstrap.js#L603">here</a> for what we did for the Dropdown plugin.  And <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/blob/master/media/jui/js/bootstrap.js#L496">this line</a> fixes a conflict we ran into with MooTools and jQuery in the Collapse plugin.</p>', '2012-10-16 21:39:51'),
(9517448, 490, 'infograf768', '<p>Committed with eclipse. Thanks.</p>', '2012-10-17 06:39:49'),
(9519661, 500, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed with eclipse. Thanks</p>', '2012-10-17 08:28:57'),
(9522132, 504, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker on joomlacode with precise instructions to reproduce the issue with default core or providing an extension to test and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-10-17 10:06:31'),
(9522213, 475, 'infograf768', '<p>If a patch is proposed,  please create a PR, a tracker on joomlacode and cross-reference in the PR</p>', '2012-10-17 10:09:51'),
(9522242, 464, 'svanschu', '<p>It is a 3.0.1</p>\n\n<p>Joomla! Version  Joomla! 3.0.1 Stable [ Ember ] 09-October-2012 14:00 GMT<br>\nJoomla! Platform Version     Joomla Platform 12.2.0 Stable [ Neil Armstrong ] 21-September-2012 00:00 GMT</p>', '2012-10-17 10:11:07'),
(9522502, 464, 'svanschu', '<p>The Bug is inside 3.0.1 but with latest of git it is fixed â€¦</p>', '2012-10-17 10:22:50'),
(9524539, 504, 'obsidev', '<p>If you want to have the error, just but this code:<br>\n$_SESSION[''test''] = new stdClass();</p>\n\n<h2></h2>\n\n<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29517">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29517</a></p>', '2012-10-17 11:54:52'),
(9554771, 488, 'okonomiyaki3000', '<p>This seems like a good idea. </p>', '2012-10-18 06:47:47'),
(9565822, 230, 'spignataro', '<p>Still looking to see this resolved in the upcoming version of Joomla! 2.5.x - can I please have a statement as to why this bug will not be accepted or at least even looked at?</p>', '2012-10-18 14:13:29'),
(9568514, 472, 'juliopontes', '<p>move pull for <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/505" class="issue-link" title="content router fix ">joomla/joomla-cms#505</a></p>', '2012-10-18 15:25:18'),
(9572374, 230, 'spignataro', '<p>Moved to proper tracker. <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29526">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29526</a></p>', '2012-10-18 17:07:26'),
(9598977, 506, 'infograf768', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29530">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29530</a></p>', '2012-10-19 12:16:12'),
(9602204, 123, 'pollen8', '<p>Closing this as the pull request is out of data - a new patch has been submitted on the tracker</p>', '2012-10-19 14:10:49'),
(9606040, 507, 'infograf768', '<p>Please create a tracker in joomlacode and cross reference here.</p>', '2012-10-19 15:51:06'),
(9614727, 510, 'shumisha', '<p>Closing. Already fixed by Benjamin: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=29420">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=8103&amp;tracker_item_id=29420</a></p>', '2012-10-19 19:23:24'),
(9617550, 475, 'waveywhite', '<p>The current suggested fix avoids the conflict but the standard way of auto-starting a Bootstrap carousel no longer works.</p>\n\n<p>I''d like to suggest an alternative approach. Please don''t hobble jQuery, It''s better to hobble Mootools as developers will be using jQuery with Bootstrap and won''t like it that the standard code doesn''t work. How about this instead, after the Mootools include?</p>\n\n<pre><code>    Element.implement({\n        slide: function(how, mode){\n            return this;\n        }\n    });\n</code></pre>', '2012-10-19 20:35:09'),
(9619860, 507, 'mahagr', '<p>Unfortunately $item comes potentially from untrusted source, which means that the values may not be integers even if you expect them to be. To prevent SQL injection, you should at least cast the values to integers before using them in SQL query.</p>\n\n<p>So instead of fixing anything (code wasn''t broken), you introduced potential SQL injection vulnerability if your fix is combined with a bad input to the function.</p>', '2012-10-19 20:57:41'),
(9620009, 509, 'mahagr', '<p>Looks good to me.</p>', '2012-10-19 20:59:08'),
(9620648, 507, 'mbabker', '<p>This behavior should also be changed in the MySQL class to keep things consistent.  I''d also suggest ensuring the values are type casted just to be safe since the plgFinder group is setting these values based on what a user creates.</p>', '2012-10-19 21:05:26'),
(9622219, 475, 'youjoomla', '<p>SWEET! much cleaner and no loops </p>\n\n<p>window.addEvent(''domready'', function(){<br>\nif (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'' &amp;&amp; typeof MooTools != ''undefined'' ) {<br><br>\n  Element.implement({<br>\n        slide: function(how, mode){<br>\n            return this;<br>\n        }<br>\n    }); <br>\n}<br>\nÂ });<br><br>\nadd in head or file </p>\n\n<p>thank you, I would rather go for this .</p>', '2012-10-19 22:05:00'),
(9629541, 506, 'infograf768', '<p>Thanks. Fixed with eclipse.</p>', '2012-10-20 09:24:09'),
(9632046, 475, 'jwhelan72', '<p>OK.  So there are two ways to prevent this conflict.  Can someone add a note about the relative merits of each and when one should be chosen over the other?  I''m new to javascript and often see the solutions to these kinds of problems without the all-important ''why use this?'' or ''why does it work?''.  And, thanks for these too.  It''s made my Joomla implementation go a lot smoother.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>JW</li>\n</ul>', '2012-10-20 15:00:01'),
(9634200, 497, 'shumisha', '<p>Hi<br>\nI think this could be made more generic, and prepare for future improvement. For instance:<br>\n1 - add a type param instead of $custom<br>\npublic static function addFilter($label, $name, $options, $noDefault = false, $type = ''select'')<br>\n2 - then in layout file:</p>\n\n<h4><?php echo JText::_(''JSEARCH_FILTER_LABEL'');?></h4>\n\n<pre><code>        &lt;?php foreach ($displayData-&gt;filters as $filter) :\n          switch($filter[''type'']) :\n            case ''select'': ?&gt;\n\n            &lt;label for="&lt;?php echo $filter[''name'']; ?&gt;" class="element-invisible"&gt;&lt;?php echo $filter[''label'']; ?&gt;&lt;/label&gt;\n            &lt;select name="&lt;?php echo $filter[''name'']; ?&gt;" id="&lt;?php echo $filter[''name'']; ?&gt;" class="span12 small" onchange="this.form.submit()"&gt;\n                &lt;?php if (!$filter[''noDefault'']) : ?&gt;\n                    &lt;option value=""&gt;&lt;?php echo $filter[''label'']; ?&gt;&lt;/option&gt;\n                &lt;?php endif; ?&gt;\n                &lt;?php echo $filter[''options'']; ?&gt;\n            &lt;/select&gt;\n            &lt;?php \n            break;\n            case ''custom'':\n                echo $filter[''custom''];\n            break;\n\n            // maybe more filter types in the future\n            endswitch;\n            ?&gt;\n            &lt;hr class="hr-condensed" /&gt;\n        &lt;?php endforeach; ?&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note that in the case of real "custom" filter, I think we should not add any markup at all ourselves (ie no ) as this is really up to the caller, and maybe they don''t want a label (this could be used to display an help text for instance or something else.<br>\nSo maybe we also want to add a simple<br>\npublic static function addCustomFilter( $customFilter)<br>\nto let extensions add real raw filter</p>\n\n<p>What do you think?</p>', '2012-10-20 17:57:38'),
(9641111, 507, 'gpongelli', '<p>Added type cast and changed mysql''s driver too.<br>\nJoomlacode tracker is <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29551">#29551</a></p>', '2012-10-21 09:40:31'),
(9641587, 507, 'mahagr', '<p>Changes aren''t identical -- MySQL is both casting and escaping vs just casting the variables.</p>', '2012-10-21 11:00:48'),
(9642078, 507, 'gpongelli', '<p>I don''t know if MySQL needs quote or not when updating/inserting double<br>\nvalue, so I''ve kept existing and working code, adding check and cast only.<br>\nPostgreSQL doesn''t need quote instead.</p>', '2012-10-21 12:17:33'),
(9642978, 475, 'waveywhite', '<p>Others may like to add their penny''s worth. This is how I''d sum it up.</p>\n\n<p>Method <a href="https://github.com/JTracker/jissues/issues/1" class="issue-link" title="Sorting and Filtering options">#1</a> <br>\nif (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'' &amp;&amp; typeof MooTools != ''undefined'' ) {<br>\n// both present , kill jquery slide for carousel class<br>\n(function($) { <br>\n       $(document).ready(function(){<br>\n        $(''.carousel'').each(function(index, element) {<br>\n                $(this)[index].slide = null;<br>\n               });<br>\n         });<br>\n })(jQuery);<br>\n}</p>\n\n<p>This disables the jQuery carousel (if your carousel has a class of .carousel). Gets around the conflict but has the side-effect of disabling the carousel slide animation. Other possible issues is this only works for carousels with a particular class and it features a loop (hence more processing).</p>\n\n<h1></h1>\n\n<p>Method  <a href="https://github.com/JTracker/jissues/issues/2" class="issue-link" title="Authentication with GitHub">#2</a><br>\nwindow.addEvent(''domready'', function(){<br>\nif (typeof jQuery != ''undefined'' &amp;&amp; typeof MooTools != ''undefined'' ) {</p>\n\n<p>Element.implement({<br>\nslide: function(how, mode){<br>\nreturn this;<br>\n}<br>\n});<br>\n}<br>\n });</p>\n\n<p>This turns-off the Moo-tools Fx.Slider feature by overriding a function so that it does nothing. Benefits are that it allows the normal Bootstrap carousel function to do it''s thing, doesn''t need a loop and doesn''t rely on calling your carousel by a particular class. Only possible downside is if you''re relying on Mootools Fx.slider as it now won''t do anything. </p>\n\n<p>Summary:<br>\nIf you''re using Bootstrap use method 2. If you want Mootools slider you''re probably not using Bootstrap so Method 2 wouldn''t trigger anyway.</p>', '2012-10-21 14:19:08'),
(9653978, 507, 'mahagr', '<p>MySQL doesn''t need quote either.</p>', '2012-10-22 06:48:13'),
(9654672, 517, 'gpongelli', '<p>Have you tried to add "DEFAULT '''' " to column definition, without this change ?<br>\nIn this case it''s maintained consistency with MySQL, the result is the same without doing whenever code change like this.</p>', '2012-10-22 07:28:22'),
(9654711, 507, 'gpongelli', '<p>I''ll add a commit to fix it this evening.</p>', '2012-10-22 07:29:50'),
(9661199, 475, 'youjoomla', '<p>nice explanation  waveywhite  , the 2nd method can be perfected by checking the .carousel class, as it is expected more or less , not to have 2 featured sliders on same page , this way we don''t have to disable Mootools FX.slide completely since there are plenty of sliders out there that are using it <br>\nsimple:<br>\nif( $(''.carousel'') ){</p>\n\n<p>// method 2<br>\n}</p>\n\n<p>would do the trick</p>', '2012-10-22 12:05:07'),
(9669590, 517, 'vietvh', '<p>Yes, adding default value is fine however I checked the DDL of MySQL, PostgreSql and SqlAzure, they do not have default value for those fields, adding default value should be done for those 3 and I just do not have SqlAzure at hand to test so I went with the PHP fix, just faster for me.</p>', '2012-10-22 16:04:14'),
