(11674753, 611, 'nickanti', '<p>?<br>\nfor what?</p>\n\n<p>I have opened tracker items for everything.</p>\n\n<p>On 25 Î”ÎµÎº 2012, at 3:06 Î¼.Î¼., javier gomez wrote:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks Nick! ^_^</p>\n\n<p>Can you open a tracker in joomlacode <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/</a> and cross reference it so the Bug Squad can test it?</p>\n\n<p>Thanks</p>\n\n<p>â€”<br>\nReply to this email directly or view it on GitHub.</p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-12-25 17:23:59'),
(11674797, 611, 'nickanti', '<p><a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=11410&amp;tracker_item_id=29848">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_id=11410&amp;tracker_item_id=29848</a></p>\n\n<p>On 25 Î”ÎµÎº 2012, at 3:06 Î¼.Î¼., javier gomez wrote:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks Nick! ^_^</p>\n\n<p>Can you open a tracker in joomlacode <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/</a> and cross reference it so the Bug Squad can test it?</p>\n\n<p>Thanks</p>\n\n<p>â€”<br>\nReply to this email directly or view it on GitHub.</p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-12-25 17:29:52'),
(11674866, 611, 'elkuku', '<blockquote>\n<p>for what? </p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>For reference ;)</p>\n\n<p>Hopefully this will be "unified" in some future..</p>\n\n<p>Thanks for your patience ;)</p>', '2012-12-25 17:37:58'),
(11682425, 576, 'infograf768', '<p>Fixed with eclipse after adding Hathor.</p>', '2012-12-26 07:56:56'),
(11684227, 461, 'Bakual', '<p>Compiled the CSS files using generatecss.php.<br>\nAlso trackeritem is here for reference: <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29718">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=29718</a></p>', '2012-12-26 10:29:18'),
(11713881, 610, 'infograf768', '<p>Missing changes in beez3.</p>', '2012-12-27 17:44:22'),
(11713988, 610, 'nickanti', '<p>This pull request is no longer valid - try #612 instead.</p>', '2012-12-27 17:51:06'),
(11741770, 3, 'mbabker', '<p>I think <a href="https://github.com/JTracker/jissues/commit/06157ecf122d64c81de449118b49ed4092297781" class="commit-link"><tt>06157ec</tt></a> has this one covered quite well, so closing the oldest open item here ;-)</p>', '2012-12-28 21:15:08'),
(11741987, 116, 'mbabker', '<p>Another solution for including jQuery was added with the Bootstrap work.  Closing this item.</p>', '2012-12-28 21:24:22'),
(11742037, 134, 'mbabker', '<p>In the CMS, they aren''t used as far as I''m aware.  Some changes to the constants have occurred in the Platform.  Any further discussion should go on there.</p>', '2012-12-28 21:26:53'),
(11742268, 228, 'mbabker', '<p>If this is still something you want to do, it needs updated to master.</p>', '2012-12-28 21:38:40'),
(11742504, 228, 'dongilbert', '<p>It was suggested that it may not be as useful now that multi-upload is available. So I''ve resolved to leaving it in a custom override for my clients and that it doesn''t <em>need</em> to be in core. You can close the PR or I can once I get to an actual computer. </p>\n\n<p>Sent from my iPhone</p>\n\n<p>On Dec 28, 2012, at 4:38 PM, Michael Babker <a href="mailto:notifications@github.com">notifications@github.com</a> wrote:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>If this is still something you want to do, it needs updated to master.</p>\n\n<p>â€”<br>\nReply to this email directly or view it on GitHub.</p>\n</blockquote>', '2012-12-28 21:51:43'),
(11744226, 618, 'jmcameron', '<p>Please see:  <a href="http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=27699">http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=27699</a> (<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/618" class="issue-link" title="[#29864] Many properties missing when triggering onContentPrepare">joomla/joomla-cms#618</a>) for a similar issue.  It would be great if we could agree that $row is always the full object, not just the text...</p>\n\n<p>-Jonathan</p>', '2012-12-28 23:24:16'),
(11749489, 335, 'dongilbert', '<p>This was fixed in version 12.2 of the platform.</p>', '2012-12-29 06:16:53'),
(11749566, 13, 'dongilbert', '<p>Dependencies are not currently supported, but were added for that possibility in the future, according to Ian here: <a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/joomla-dev-platform/SSfpetLPESI/vuht__60B8YJ">https://groups.google.com/d/msg/joomla-dev-platform/SSfpetLPESI/vuht__60B8YJ</a></p>', '2012-12-29 06:29:49'),
(11750299, 625, 'CristinaSolana', '<p>Hi Nikolai,</p>\n\n<p>I agree the style and readability there could be improved. I would do this in a separate pull request for two reasons:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>It is unrelated to the issue I was fixing with incomplete class names.</p></li>\n<li><p>There are others, for example, on lines 139 and 183. A PR that changes all of these so that readability is improved, but also consistency is maintained throughout the file.</p></li>\n</ol><p>I will gladly do that tomorrow and put in another PR. Will also look around and see if it is present in any other files within the template. :)</p>', '2012-12-29 08:10:28'),
(11750387, 609, 'nickanti', '<p>closing this because it has been included in 614</p>', '2012-12-29 08:26:00'),
(11750398, 611, 'nickanti', '<p>this has been closed in favor of 614</p>', '2012-12-29 08:27:21'),
(11750403, 613, 'nickanti', '<p>closed in favor of 614</p>', '2012-12-29 08:27:54'),
(11750409, 584, 'nickanti', '<p>closed in favor of 615</p>', '2012-12-29 08:28:55'),
(11750417, 610, 'nickanti', '<p>closed in favor of 612</p>', '2012-12-29 08:30:26'),
(11753796, 534, 'brunobatista', '<p>Now I use Joomla! 3.0<br>\nLanguages: Ingles and Portuguese.<br>\nNormal steps.</p>', '2012-12-29 15:03:20'),
